1
00:00:02,063 --> 00:00:03,873
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

2
00:00:03,873 --> 00:00:07,293
The people with sharp romance
radars have gathered.

3
00:00:07,293 --> 00:00:10,353
[Heart Signal 5 starts now]

4
00:00:10,353 --> 00:00:15,253
A special predictor joined us
to fill in for Tsuki today.

5
00:00:15,253 --> 00:00:16,803
SinB is here.

6
00:00:16,803 --> 00:00:19,943
Hello, I'm SinB. Nice to meet you.

7
00:00:19,943 --> 00:00:21,253
[Nice to meet you]

8
00:00:21,253 --> 00:00:22,453
How big a dating show fan are you?

9
00:00:22,453 --> 00:00:26,593
I've been watching Heart Signal
since Season 1.

10
00:00:26,593 --> 00:00:32,153
I watched other shows whenever
I needed a dopamine hit.

11
00:00:32,153 --> 00:00:34,843
- You think of it as a drug.
- That's right.

12
00:00:34,843 --> 00:00:38,793
I tried to predict as a viewer,
but I don't think I'm that good.

13
00:00:38,793 --> 00:00:41,103
Just think the opposite of Roy.

14
00:00:41,103 --> 00:00:45,133
I know. He didn't seem so good at predicting.

15
00:00:45,133 --> 00:00:48,453
I'm just acting. I do it on purpose.

16
00:00:48,453 --> 00:00:51,093
- Acting?
- What a great actor.

17
00:00:51,093 --> 00:00:55,073
Last week, they had official dates
in Tokushima, Japan.

18
00:00:55,073 --> 00:00:57,093
The women chose their dates.

19
00:00:57,093 --> 00:00:59,503
Gyu Ri chose Seo Won.

20
00:00:59,503 --> 00:01:01,273
The suspension bridge.

21
00:01:02,133 --> 00:01:05,423
- Hold my hand.
- I want these two to end up together.

22
00:01:05,423 --> 00:01:09,323
Gyu Ri seems a lot more charming
when she's with him.

23
00:01:09,323 --> 00:01:14,233
Seo Won is so cool
when he's devoted to someone.

24
00:01:14,233 --> 00:01:17,673
He started getting jealous
when they ate together.

25
00:01:17,673 --> 00:01:22,633
He needs to express
his feelings more aggressively.

26
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:25,293
Right. That's true. He's too nice.

27
00:01:25,293 --> 00:01:27,963
Jun Hyeon and Yu Gyeong went on a date.

28
00:01:27,963 --> 00:01:31,083
They kept saying, "Me, too. You, too?"

29
00:01:31,083 --> 00:01:35,313
Both of their ideal types are people
who are good with chopsticks.

30
00:01:35,313 --> 00:01:39,073
And he spoke directly during the meal.

31
00:01:39,073 --> 00:01:43,003
I just think I've been noticing you the most.

32
00:01:43,003 --> 00:01:45,593
- That's how I feel.
- Coming from Jun Hyeon.

33
00:01:45,593 --> 00:01:47,703
He's not good at expressing his feelings.

34
00:01:47,703 --> 00:01:50,333
I got a feeling that Yu Gyeong

35
00:01:50,333 --> 00:01:56,063
might start considering both
Jun Hyeon and Wu Yeol.

36
00:01:56,063 --> 00:01:58,683
The person most worried about Yu Gyeong

37
00:01:58,683 --> 00:02:01,043
is Shin Seung Hun, who's not here.

38
00:02:01,043 --> 00:02:02,983
- He's so...
- He's a huge fan...

39
00:02:02,983 --> 00:02:05,593
He's a huge fan of Heart Signal.

40
00:02:05,593 --> 00:02:07,313
Acting cool, he asked,

41
00:02:07,313 --> 00:02:10,603
"Is Yu Gyeong doing okay this week?"

42
00:02:10,603 --> 00:02:11,903
[Hehe]

43
00:02:11,903 --> 00:02:15,793
Please tell him to date instead.

44
00:02:15,793 --> 00:02:19,833
And Wu Yeol had a date with So Yun.

45
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:22,143
- The rings.
- The controversial rings.

46
00:02:22,143 --> 00:02:25,873
He didn't suggest getting
matching rings. Let's be clear.

47
00:02:25,873 --> 00:02:28,423
It just happened so naturally.

48
00:02:28,423 --> 00:02:31,023
It would've been awkward for him to say no.

49
00:02:31,023 --> 00:02:32,403
I know. It would've been.

50
00:02:32,403 --> 00:02:34,533
He couldn't say, "Don't buy it."

51
00:02:34,533 --> 00:02:38,183
Asking her not to get matching ones
would've embarrassed her.

52
00:02:38,183 --> 00:02:42,053
And it's natural that So Yun
would want to brag about it.

53
00:02:42,053 --> 00:02:44,513
It's understandable that she did that.

54
00:02:44,513 --> 00:02:46,403
I would've been totally mistaken.

55
00:02:46,403 --> 00:02:51,403
Getting matching rings is like asking
someone to marry them, right?

56
00:02:51,403 --> 00:02:55,273
Seong Min and Min Ju's date was so dramatic.

57
00:02:55,273 --> 00:02:58,173
It was nice how honest they were.

58
00:02:58,173 --> 00:02:59,853
Am I one of the two?

59
00:02:59,853 --> 00:03:02,163
She asked that by sacrificing her pride.

60
00:03:02,163 --> 00:03:06,393
Seong Min said something that
was straight out of a movie.

61
00:03:06,393 --> 00:03:09,403
I wanted this moment to last forever.

62
00:03:09,403 --> 00:03:14,093
He seemed moved by how much she liked him.

63
00:03:14,093 --> 00:03:20,033
Let's see what would happen
at Signal House after the trip.

64
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,933
I'm so curious what will happen.

65
00:03:21,933 --> 00:03:25,833
[On the way back to Signal House]

66
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:29,123
[Wu Yeol's car]

67
00:03:29,123 --> 00:03:34,063
Do you like driving quietly
or while chatting?

68
00:03:34,063 --> 00:03:36,053
I like chatting.

69
00:03:36,053 --> 00:03:39,463
- I'd fall asleep if it were quiet.
- You can't.

70
00:03:44,743 --> 00:03:46,183
[Glancing]

71
00:03:46,723 --> 00:03:48,603
The ring. The ring.

72
00:03:48,603 --> 00:03:52,483
[Noticing Wu Yeol's hand]

73
00:03:53,003 --> 00:03:55,503
[He didn't wear the ring]

74
00:03:55,503 --> 00:03:58,173
Wu Yeol's ring is gone.

75
00:03:59,383 --> 00:04:01,753
Gosh, it's bothering her.

76
00:04:08,933 --> 00:04:11,523
- She's bothered by it, right?
- Of course.

77
00:04:11,523 --> 00:04:13,753
[Feeling conflicted]

78
00:04:16,703 --> 00:04:19,103
What time do you leave and get back tomorrow?

79
00:04:19,103 --> 00:04:23,093
I'll leave at eight and get back at two.

80
00:04:23,093 --> 00:04:25,133
- What for?
- For a move.

81
00:04:25,133 --> 00:04:27,643
- On your own? To a new place?
- No, the office.

82
00:04:27,643 --> 00:04:29,813
- Your office is moving?
- Yes.

83
00:04:31,903 --> 00:04:35,243
- You're coming back at two?
- Yes.

84
00:04:35,243 --> 00:04:37,593
What are you all doing tomorrow?

85
00:04:37,593 --> 00:04:41,193
- I'm going to the hospital tomorrow.
- Hospital? What time?

86
00:04:41,193 --> 00:04:42,993
Around four o'clock.

87
00:04:42,993 --> 00:04:45,473
Around four? I see.

88
00:04:45,473 --> 00:04:47,243
She wanted to ask Wu Yeol.

89
00:04:47,243 --> 00:04:49,383
- What about you, Wu Yeol?
- Me?

90
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:52,483
I'll play even harder.

91
00:04:53,403 --> 00:04:55,583
Fighting, fighting, fighting.

92
00:04:56,473 --> 00:04:59,373
[Does Wu Yeol have a plan tomorrow?]

93
00:04:59,373 --> 00:05:02,643
What was your favorite moment in Japan?

94
00:05:05,473 --> 00:05:07,093
Me?

95
00:05:07,093 --> 00:05:10,233
When we took the Reze photo.

96
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:14,853
[Seo Won took a photo
of Gyu Ri looking like Reze]

97
00:05:14,853 --> 00:05:17,723
- When we took the Reze photo.
- The Reze photo?

98
00:05:18,683 --> 00:05:22,933
[They're having a private conversation]

99
00:05:28,753 --> 00:05:30,903
She keeps checking his reaction.

100
00:05:30,903 --> 00:05:33,093
[Glancing]

101
00:05:39,923 --> 00:05:42,673
He's a great driver, by the way.

102
00:05:42,673 --> 00:05:46,123
- Who?
- Wu Yeol.

103
00:05:47,983 --> 00:05:51,603
- Do you feel comfortable?
- Yes, totally.

104
00:05:51,603 --> 00:05:55,573
- Get some sleep, then. Sleep.
- Like a bed.

105
00:05:55,573 --> 00:05:58,593
He's jealous. He's jealous.

106
00:06:02,753 --> 00:06:04,543
Will you choose me?

107
00:06:07,573 --> 00:06:11,663
To be honest, I don't want to do
anything with everyone there.

108
00:06:14,073 --> 00:06:15,983
I want to pick a separate time...

109
00:06:15,983 --> 00:06:17,773
Either watch separately...

110
00:06:21,053 --> 00:06:24,243
You know the movie with
that actor, Koo Kyo Hwan?

111
00:06:24,243 --> 00:06:26,293
- "Once We Were Us"?
- Yes.

112
00:06:27,293 --> 00:06:29,063
I want to see that.

113
00:06:29,063 --> 00:06:32,163
But I'm afraid
it will leave the theaters soon.

114
00:06:32,163 --> 00:06:35,273
[She made an effort,
but Wu Yeol didn't respond]

115
00:06:36,433 --> 00:06:39,553
[Their feelings are getting tangled up]

116
00:06:39,553 --> 00:06:42,253
- Look at her expression.
- It's so complicated for everyone.

117
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:48,243
[Jun Hyeon's car]

118
00:06:48,243 --> 00:06:51,403
Wow, what's with the song choice?

119
00:06:51,403 --> 00:06:54,463
Their taste in music is unusual, too.

120
00:06:55,553 --> 00:06:57,813
The genres are all over the place.

121
00:06:57,813 --> 00:07:00,483
- Is this yours, Hyung?
- I only have one.

122
00:07:00,483 --> 00:07:06,023
It's an unorganized playlist with everything.

123
00:07:06,023 --> 00:07:08,373
You just added everything you like.

124
00:07:10,863 --> 00:07:12,683
"1:05." That's my favorite song.

125
00:07:12,683 --> 00:07:14,373
- Really?
- I mean it.

126
00:07:14,373 --> 00:07:17,553
[The song he listened to with Yu Gyeong]

127
00:07:18,523 --> 00:07:22,673
I just think I've been...

128
00:07:24,073 --> 00:07:27,193
noticing you the most. That's how I feel.

129
00:07:27,193 --> 00:07:29,483
[He expressed
his feelings carefully last night]

130
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:33,643
He made an effort.

131
00:07:33,643 --> 00:07:35,303
[Glancing]

132
00:07:35,303 --> 00:07:36,043
[Glancing again]

133
00:07:37,543 --> 00:07:39,143
[Humming]

134
00:07:39,143 --> 00:07:42,153
That can be so effective.

135
00:07:43,293 --> 00:07:48,223
I sometimes feel like playing the guitar.

136
00:07:48,223 --> 00:07:51,073
- I can play along.
- You play the guitar?

137
00:07:51,073 --> 00:07:53,823
- Can you play this on the guitar?
- Of course, I can.

138
00:07:53,823 --> 00:07:56,933
Bring it and show off upstairs.

139
00:07:56,933 --> 00:07:58,603
I know. Bring it tomorrow.

140
00:07:58,603 --> 00:08:00,873
Gosh, should I do it?

141
00:08:00,873 --> 00:08:05,573
[Who will he be performing for?]

142
00:08:06,153 --> 00:08:08,433
- I'll actually have ramen.
- Ramen?

143
00:08:08,433 --> 00:08:10,673
- Let's make eight packets.
- I love that.

144
00:08:10,673 --> 00:08:13,733
Add eggs and scallions, too.

145
00:08:14,673 --> 00:08:17,363
It must feel like they're back home.

146
00:08:17,363 --> 00:08:21,003
[They arrived at the house at night]

147
00:08:21,003 --> 00:08:23,303
- Thank you.
- He's helping her.

148
00:08:23,303 --> 00:08:26,253
We're back. We're finally back.

149
00:08:26,253 --> 00:08:27,413
[The house is feeling lively again]

150
00:08:27,413 --> 00:08:29,843
The slippers are first-come, first-served.

151
00:08:29,843 --> 00:08:31,463
Where are they?

152
00:08:31,463 --> 00:08:33,953
Wow, how nice.

153
00:08:33,953 --> 00:08:36,003
I missed this place.

154
00:08:39,513 --> 00:08:41,413
[Glancing]

155
00:08:46,663 --> 00:08:49,843
Ramen sounds amazing right now.

156
00:08:49,843 --> 00:08:51,403
Do you want some?

157
00:08:51,403 --> 00:08:53,033
Brothy ramen?

158
00:08:55,523 --> 00:08:57,213
Diet ramen?

159
00:08:57,213 --> 00:09:00,463
Diet ramen, my foot.

160
00:09:02,493 --> 00:09:04,813
Let's just eat first.

161
00:09:04,813 --> 00:09:08,503
[Her first attempt at connection failed]

162
00:09:08,503 --> 00:09:11,503
Time goes by so fast.

163
00:09:14,063 --> 00:09:16,343
[Putting on]

164
00:09:16,343 --> 00:09:19,723
[Wu Yeol is tying Seong Min's apron]

165
00:09:19,723 --> 00:09:21,733
Are you making something?

166
00:09:21,733 --> 00:09:23,783
No, I'll take out the food trash.

167
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:29,483
[Hurried]

168
00:09:30,683 --> 00:09:33,313
[Eyesight regained]

169
00:09:33,313 --> 00:09:35,653
This, too. I'll take it out.

170
00:09:35,653 --> 00:09:37,953
[Yu Gyeong is back in the kitchen]

171
00:09:41,463 --> 00:09:43,093
[Concerned]

172
00:09:48,373 --> 00:09:50,123
Let me hold it. Let me hold it.

173
00:09:50,123 --> 00:09:52,843
A lot of the food expired.

174
00:09:53,673 --> 00:09:57,753
Yu Gyeong, I think we should toss the bread.

175
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:04,123
The food waste is piling up. Seriously.

176
00:10:05,193 --> 00:10:07,783
Is it falling again?

177
00:10:08,803 --> 00:10:12,693
- Did it get thinner?
- Just the right arm, I think.

178
00:10:12,693 --> 00:10:16,983
Fix this, too.
I think my right arm got thinner.

179
00:10:16,983 --> 00:10:19,433
[Second attempt failed]

180
00:10:33,973 --> 00:10:36,573
You must've had a hard time.

181
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:41,953
I wanted to keep it a secret forever.

182
00:10:46,173 --> 00:10:48,723
[Comforting]

183
00:11:00,643 --> 00:11:06,433
[The night before the trip]

184
00:11:06,433 --> 00:11:11,693
[Yu Gyeong is in the Self Talk room]

185
00:11:11,693 --> 00:11:14,693
She likes him, but she feels anxious.

186
00:11:17,013 --> 00:11:21,113
[Hesitant]

187
00:11:27,443 --> 00:11:32,003
I'll take the path even if it's thorny.

188
00:11:33,773 --> 00:11:35,433
Fighting.

189
00:11:50,273 --> 00:11:54,263
[And the next day]

190
00:12:01,513 --> 00:12:03,703
[Mouth drying]

191
00:12:14,583 --> 00:12:16,563
[Staring]

192
00:12:19,593 --> 00:12:21,103
[Glancing]

193
00:12:29,033 --> 00:12:31,673
I haven't been to a movie theater
in a long time.

194
00:12:32,483 --> 00:12:36,403
[Wu Yeol spoke first]

195
00:12:38,533 --> 00:12:43,643
We can't see a movie
if we come back on Saturday.

196
00:12:43,643 --> 00:12:47,473
Why not? When do they stop showing the movie?

197
00:12:47,473 --> 00:12:48,923
I don't know.

198
00:12:48,923 --> 00:12:50,733
Why can't we see it?

199
00:12:50,733 --> 00:12:52,503
You wanted to see it this week.

200
00:12:52,503 --> 00:12:54,683
We can see it on Sunday.

201
00:13:00,423 --> 00:13:03,103
I'm curious about the movie.

202
00:13:03,103 --> 00:13:06,063
[Smiling]

203
00:13:06,063 --> 00:13:09,053
Should we go see it? I'm free.

204
00:13:09,053 --> 00:13:11,213
It's a date.

205
00:13:11,213 --> 00:13:15,423
- Yes.
- Fine, I won't talk to you. Got it.

206
00:13:15,423 --> 00:13:17,513
[Smiling]

207
00:13:22,543 --> 00:13:25,253
Did you turn on Airplane Mode?

208
00:13:25,253 --> 00:13:26,793
No.

209
00:13:27,503 --> 00:13:29,343
I'm wearing falsies.

210
00:13:29,343 --> 00:13:32,033
[Staring]

211
00:13:36,243 --> 00:13:38,133
Look at him, laughing.

212
00:13:41,843 --> 00:13:44,083
Let me do it. You did enough.

213
00:13:46,443 --> 00:13:49,423
[Seong Min is going to the second floor]

214
00:13:51,953 --> 00:13:53,343
Gosh...

215
00:13:58,323 --> 00:14:00,483
This goes here.

216
00:14:04,163 --> 00:14:08,223
- I was washing my dishes anyway.
- Thank you.

217
00:14:08,223 --> 00:14:10,793
What? He likes doing the dishes.

218
00:14:10,793 --> 00:14:14,293
- Really?
- It's his hobby.

219
00:14:30,763 --> 00:14:32,083
[Getting up]

220
00:14:33,343 --> 00:14:34,583
[Peeping]

221
00:14:37,693 --> 00:14:38,933
[Hesitant]

222
00:14:38,933 --> 00:14:40,623
Why? Why? Why?

223
00:14:41,623 --> 00:14:43,093
[Organizing shoes]

224
00:14:43,653 --> 00:14:44,733
[Peeping]

225
00:14:48,483 --> 00:14:51,083
Unbelievable. Don't back down.

226
00:14:51,083 --> 00:14:52,893
You're just cleaning up, right?

227
00:14:52,893 --> 00:14:54,653
- Huh?
- Cleaning up?

228
00:14:54,653 --> 00:14:56,723
- Are you done?
- Yes.

229
00:14:56,723 --> 00:14:58,853
[Staring]

230
00:15:02,753 --> 00:15:04,503
Tomorrow?

231
00:15:04,503 --> 00:15:06,663
Want to see a movie?

232
00:15:06,663 --> 00:15:09,613
- She did it.
- "Once We Were Us."

233
00:15:09,613 --> 00:15:11,093
- Huh?
- Are there tickets?

234
00:15:11,093 --> 00:15:12,803
There are tons of seats left.

235
00:15:12,803 --> 00:15:15,083
[Excited]

236
00:15:15,083 --> 00:15:16,723
Do you watch movies?

237
00:15:17,873 --> 00:15:19,603
"Once We Were Us"?

238
00:15:19,603 --> 00:15:21,153
Should we watch a movie this week?

239
00:15:21,153 --> 00:15:24,003
I really want to see the movie.

240
00:15:24,003 --> 00:15:26,003
Why can't we see it?

241
00:15:26,003 --> 00:15:28,413
I'm curious about the movie.

242
00:15:28,413 --> 00:15:30,113
Should we go see it?

243
00:15:32,733 --> 00:15:36,703
I'll go to the gym earlier. I need to depuff.

244
00:15:38,143 --> 00:15:39,673
Yu Gyeong is excited right now.

245
00:15:39,673 --> 00:15:46,243
[They're giddy from the excitement tonight]

246
00:15:47,733 --> 00:15:49,053
- Does that work?
- Yes.

247
00:15:49,053 --> 00:15:51,493
It looks like a baby cradle.

248
00:15:51,493 --> 00:15:53,543
You aren't going to fall back, right?

249
00:15:53,543 --> 00:15:55,563
I'm fine.

250
00:15:56,253 --> 00:15:58,713
Am I one of the two?

251
00:16:02,933 --> 00:16:05,503
You are. You're one of them.

252
00:16:05,503 --> 00:16:08,203
[Sitting far away]

253
00:16:08,203 --> 00:16:13,753
[Things got awkward
between them after their talk]

254
00:16:16,903 --> 00:16:18,423
You guys are matching right now.

255
00:16:18,423 --> 00:16:21,233
- Don't copy me, seriously.
- I put this on this morning.

256
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:23,793
- Don't copy me.
- You're matching.

257
00:16:24,903 --> 00:16:28,143
Yongsan CGV or...

258
00:16:28,143 --> 00:16:31,883
- If you include the travel time...
- Is that Seo Won?

259
00:16:31,883 --> 00:16:35,103
[So Yun is heading to the first floor]

260
00:16:38,993 --> 00:16:41,843
Or should I just skip the gym?

261
00:16:41,843 --> 00:16:44,243
- Just go. We don't have to rush.
- I might get tired.

262
00:16:44,243 --> 00:16:47,603
I think it might be better to sleep in.

263
00:16:47,603 --> 00:16:50,813
- Still in the evening, then?
- We're free then.

264
00:16:50,813 --> 00:16:54,063
[Gyu Ri is heading to the first floor]

265
00:16:58,673 --> 00:16:59,663
Hey.

266
00:17:00,483 --> 00:17:01,983
- Gyu Ri is here.
- No!

267
00:17:01,983 --> 00:17:03,893
Refreshment time.

268
00:17:03,893 --> 00:17:05,303
Refreshment time.

269
00:17:05,303 --> 00:17:09,363
- Or not?
- I don't know when is a good time.

270
00:17:09,363 --> 00:17:12,223
My gosh. My gosh. Please.

271
00:17:13,163 --> 00:17:15,183
What do you think?

272
00:17:15,183 --> 00:17:16,903
[Glancing]

273
00:17:16,903 --> 00:17:19,823
- No!
- I can't do this.

274
00:17:20,783 --> 00:17:22,933
[She's bothered by the two talking]

275
00:17:22,933 --> 00:17:24,933
I can't watch.

276
00:17:24,933 --> 00:17:27,403
[Sigh]

277
00:17:28,683 --> 00:17:31,103
[The scarf she dyed with Wu Yeol]

278
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:37,463
The scarf you dyed?

279
00:17:38,463 --> 00:17:40,133
The handkerchief.

280
00:17:42,353 --> 00:17:43,493
[Glancing]

281
00:18:02,513 --> 00:18:03,183
[Tossing]

282
00:18:09,173 --> 00:18:11,953
[They're still planning the movie date]

283
00:18:12,763 --> 00:18:14,163
- Did you sleep?
- Yes.

284
00:18:14,163 --> 00:18:15,453
Good job.

285
00:18:15,453 --> 00:18:18,473
- Did you eat something?
- Cafe? A cafe?

286
00:18:18,473 --> 00:18:21,723
Good thing Seo Won is keeping her company.

287
00:18:21,723 --> 00:18:25,763
[They're in the same space,]

288
00:18:25,763 --> 00:18:28,003
[but having different conversations]

289
00:18:28,003 --> 00:18:30,903
We should grab food tomorrow.

290
00:18:32,223 --> 00:18:36,043
Let's have lunch,

291
00:18:36,043 --> 00:18:39,183
- Then, watch.
- watch the movie,

292
00:18:40,753 --> 00:18:42,913
and have dinner?

293
00:18:42,913 --> 00:18:44,603
That's basically...

294
00:18:44,603 --> 00:18:50,483
We can drink coffee during the movie.

295
00:18:50,483 --> 00:18:53,953
They're talking loudly.
They aren't whispering.

296
00:18:58,793 --> 00:19:01,353
We should plan here, too.

297
00:19:01,353 --> 00:19:02,933
Where?

298
00:19:03,933 --> 00:19:06,783
- Yongsan?
- She came close.

299
00:19:06,783 --> 00:19:09,163
My gosh! He can't talk right now.

300
00:19:09,163 --> 00:19:10,853
We have a plan, too.

301
00:19:10,853 --> 00:19:12,583
Let's talk over there.

302
00:19:12,583 --> 00:19:14,433
They want to talk next to them.

303
00:19:14,433 --> 00:19:20,723
[Wu Yeol is avoiding them]

304
00:19:21,953 --> 00:19:22,783
[Turning around]

305
00:19:25,543 --> 00:19:27,133
Nearby? It doesn't matter.

306
00:19:27,133 --> 00:19:29,983
Let's go somewhere accessible.

307
00:19:32,303 --> 00:19:35,923
- Coming back at two tomorrow?
- Huh? Yes.

308
00:19:37,813 --> 00:19:40,443
Can we plan the date?

309
00:19:40,443 --> 00:19:44,453
I wrote down the things
I want to do. A movie.

310
00:19:47,733 --> 00:19:50,233
I was thinking the same.

311
00:19:50,233 --> 00:19:51,933
I want to see it in a theater.

312
00:19:51,933 --> 00:19:54,893
We can. Why don't we do that?

313
00:19:54,893 --> 00:19:58,093
Gyu Ri will naturally watch a movie
with Seo Won.

314
00:19:58,093 --> 00:20:01,093
[Excited]

315
00:20:01,093 --> 00:20:03,873
Do you know what's nearby?

316
00:20:03,873 --> 00:20:06,453
We're the same.

317
00:20:06,453 --> 00:20:09,743
We're the same once we get down to it.

318
00:20:09,743 --> 00:20:12,693
- You're worse, Noona.
- What are you saying?

319
00:20:12,693 --> 00:20:14,163
If it gets too crowded...

320
00:20:14,163 --> 00:20:16,123
- If so...
- How about we...

321
00:20:16,123 --> 00:20:19,083
Somewhere with just a movie theater?

322
00:20:20,033 --> 00:20:22,263
Around 2:30?

323
00:20:22,263 --> 00:20:23,743
This.

324
00:20:24,603 --> 00:20:26,563
Or should we just completely...

325
00:20:26,563 --> 00:20:30,403
What do you mean, completely?

326
00:20:30,403 --> 00:20:32,843
- What time should we meet?
- Should I just stay out?

327
00:20:32,843 --> 00:20:35,033
- Wu Yeol is bothered.
- They all are.

328
00:20:35,033 --> 00:20:37,013
Do you want to come back home?

329
00:20:37,013 --> 00:20:39,693
I think I should stop by.

330
00:20:39,693 --> 00:20:41,913
- Is that so?
- Yes.

331
00:20:43,123 --> 00:20:45,813
I don't want to stop by.

332
00:20:50,563 --> 00:20:53,123
- What's this? What's going on?
- Daebak.

333
00:20:53,123 --> 00:20:58,543
[He can hear
Seo Won and Gyu Ri's conversation]

334
00:21:00,743 --> 00:21:02,283
Gosh.

335
00:21:02,283 --> 00:21:05,183
- But Yongsan...
- We have a car. How about Gangnam Station?

336
00:21:05,183 --> 00:21:07,403
The Gangnam location is nice.

337
00:21:10,803 --> 00:21:12,933
Is it nice?

338
00:21:12,933 --> 00:21:15,083
Is it still on? The one with Koo Kyo Hwan.

339
00:21:15,083 --> 00:21:18,953
It was still on when I checked last week.

340
00:21:18,953 --> 00:21:22,173
- Oh, yeah? I really want to see it.
- Me, too.

341
00:21:23,193 --> 00:21:25,453
It's my favorite genre.

342
00:21:26,613 --> 00:21:32,703
It's my second time watching
a romance movie in theaters.

343
00:21:32,703 --> 00:21:34,613
- Really?
- Yes.

344
00:21:35,563 --> 00:21:38,173
- It's not my usual choice.
- We'll do our best to watch it.

345
00:21:38,173 --> 00:21:39,943
He can't stop listening right now.

346
00:21:39,943 --> 00:21:42,383
I'm dying to see it.

347
00:21:43,553 --> 00:21:45,303
It's Jun Hyeon.

348
00:21:50,043 --> 00:21:51,223
[Glancing]

349
00:21:53,343 --> 00:21:54,813
[Pause]

350
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:57,503
- Hello.
- Where's my cup?

351
00:21:57,503 --> 00:21:59,903
[Everyone is acting awkward]

352
00:22:01,903 --> 00:22:04,053
Should we do 5:20?

353
00:22:09,153 --> 00:22:12,833
- The bell isn't ringing.
- There's no water?

354
00:22:14,733 --> 00:22:16,633
We don't have water?

355
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:19,363
Looks like it.

356
00:22:20,143 --> 00:22:22,193
Gosh.

357
00:22:26,953 --> 00:22:28,405
Should we go to the first-floor living room?

358
00:22:28,405 --> 00:22:29,523
I was just thinking that.

359
00:22:29,523 --> 00:22:32,803
- My legs are hurting.
- I'll get my phone. So I can look up stuff.

360
00:22:32,803 --> 00:22:33,933
Gosh...

361
00:22:33,933 --> 00:22:37,523
- My legs hurt.
- He won't look at her.

362
00:22:37,523 --> 00:22:39,953
Where do you want to sit?

363
00:22:39,953 --> 00:22:44,313
Is there a spot in the theater you prefer?

364
00:22:45,183 --> 00:22:47,633
Off to the side.

365
00:22:47,633 --> 00:22:50,963
Is that the cup I was using?

366
00:22:52,693 --> 00:22:56,003
How about a couple's seats like this?

367
00:22:58,783 --> 00:23:00,893
I don't know how they work.

368
00:23:00,893 --> 00:23:03,023
- Just one second.
- Okay.

369
00:23:06,663 --> 00:23:08,803
Those are you know...

370
00:23:08,803 --> 00:23:11,353
Is it like a sofa?

371
00:23:11,353 --> 00:23:12,473
They don't have this thing.

372
00:23:12,473 --> 00:23:14,643
- The divider?
- The couple's seat.

373
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:16,353
- Are they sitting there?
- What's your usual choice?

374
00:23:16,353 --> 00:23:19,383
Somewhere like this or in the center?

375
00:23:19,383 --> 00:23:22,453
I usually choose the center.

376
00:23:22,453 --> 00:23:24,283
You know what?

377
00:23:24,283 --> 00:23:25,993
The...

378
00:23:25,993 --> 00:23:27,833
[Twitch]

379
00:23:34,253 --> 00:23:35,403
Stop making faces.

380
00:23:35,403 --> 00:23:38,473
You're displaying three facial expressions.

381
00:23:38,473 --> 00:23:40,573
It's because I haven't seen you in a while.

382
00:23:40,573 --> 00:23:42,133
[Twitching]

383
00:23:42,133 --> 00:23:44,003
My eyebrows won't stay put.

384
00:23:44,003 --> 00:23:46,963
They're joking around now.

385
00:23:49,023 --> 00:23:50,513
Done.

386
00:23:52,573 --> 00:23:55,393
Gosh, what's going on?

387
00:23:57,103 --> 00:23:59,923
- Were you going to pick something up?
- I'm buying them now.

388
00:23:59,923 --> 00:24:01,283
- Are you hungry?
- Yes.

389
00:24:01,283 --> 00:24:04,303
[Gyu Ri is leaving quietly]

390
00:24:04,303 --> 00:24:07,583
We can take the rest to go.

391
00:24:07,583 --> 00:24:09,813
I don't have my phone. Can I bring it?

392
00:24:09,813 --> 00:24:11,563
Yes, of course.

393
00:24:11,563 --> 00:24:14,913
- Of course.
- It's not that.

394
00:24:24,493 --> 00:24:26,293
[The scarf she dyed with Wu Yeol]

395
00:24:33,693 --> 00:24:36,843
[So Yun is going to the first floor]

396
00:24:36,843 --> 00:24:40,333
[Jun Hyeon and Min Ju]

397
00:24:54,203 --> 00:24:56,603
- Feels nice, right?
- Yes.

398
00:24:56,603 --> 00:24:58,133
Why are you smiling?

399
00:24:58,133 --> 00:25:00,053
- It's just fascinating.
- What is?

400
00:25:00,053 --> 00:25:01,633
This place.

401
00:25:01,633 --> 00:25:03,763
It's fascinating.

402
00:25:03,763 --> 00:25:05,883
It's a fascinating place.

403
00:25:08,223 --> 00:25:09,163
Isn't it?

404
00:25:09,163 --> 00:25:11,833
I guess you don't feel any stress yet.

405
00:25:11,833 --> 00:25:15,103
- I'm just so happy right now.
- Really?

406
00:25:18,813 --> 00:25:19,713
[Chugging]

407
00:25:21,663 --> 00:25:23,743
What...

408
00:25:26,303 --> 00:25:29,143
But it's kind of...

409
00:25:29,143 --> 00:25:32,003
I thought if I told you this today,

410
00:25:33,503 --> 00:25:36,283
you might feel uncomfortable.

411
00:25:36,283 --> 00:25:39,533
So, I thought I shouldn't have to.

412
00:25:39,533 --> 00:25:43,853
[He started feeling pressured]

413
00:25:43,853 --> 00:25:46,193
- Totally.
- Totally?

414
00:25:46,193 --> 00:25:48,193
- Too much.
- Too much?

415
00:25:48,193 --> 00:25:50,533
I should just eat and sleep well for a month.

416
00:25:50,533 --> 00:25:52,193
Right.

417
00:25:52,193 --> 00:25:56,263
But it's definitely fascinating.

418
00:26:01,423 --> 00:26:04,373
We should eat and sleep well.

419
00:26:09,883 --> 00:26:11,753
This is interesting.

420
00:26:13,213 --> 00:26:14,763
Interesting?

421
00:26:17,433 --> 00:26:23,663
I didn't know you were thinking that way.

422
00:26:25,143 --> 00:26:29,003
I don't see how you could've.
Not to this extent.

423
00:26:29,003 --> 00:26:30,743
Right.

424
00:26:32,663 --> 00:26:40,863
[He expressed his feelings for Yu Gyeong]

425
00:26:45,183 --> 00:26:48,423
Why did you think of galbitang?

426
00:26:48,423 --> 00:26:51,583
I always eat galbitang whenever I'm sick.

427
00:26:51,583 --> 00:26:53,733
Do you have a routine?

428
00:26:54,683 --> 00:26:57,313
You eat one and a half bowls?

429
00:26:57,313 --> 00:26:59,783
- What did you say?
- One and a half bowls of rice?

430
00:26:59,783 --> 00:27:02,583
Yes, totally.

431
00:27:02,583 --> 00:27:04,643
I didn't have enough kkakdugi.

432
00:27:04,643 --> 00:27:08,163
I haven't seen you eat much.

433
00:27:08,163 --> 00:27:11,023
- I changed my strategy.
- To eat a lot now?

434
00:27:11,023 --> 00:27:12,383
Eat well and sleep well.

435
00:27:12,383 --> 00:27:14,113
- Nice.
- You, too?

436
00:27:14,113 --> 00:27:15,673
Let's eat and sleep well.

437
00:27:15,673 --> 00:27:17,353
We should.

438
00:27:18,723 --> 00:27:23,723
[A way to overcome complicated feelings]

439
00:27:23,723 --> 00:27:27,183
Shouldn't you get puffed up now
since you're depuffing?

440
00:27:27,183 --> 00:27:29,613
- I know.
- Should we get puffed up?

441
00:27:29,613 --> 00:27:31,783
Let's get puffed up. Only I'll depuff.

442
00:27:31,783 --> 00:27:34,773
I know. I'll be looking like this.

443
00:27:35,953 --> 00:27:37,993
What are you up to?

444
00:27:37,993 --> 00:27:40,533
- Thinking about what to eat.
- What to eat?

445
00:27:40,533 --> 00:27:42,073
What should I do with the scarf?

446
00:27:42,073 --> 00:27:43,693
She brought that over.

447
00:27:43,693 --> 00:27:45,883
You want to hang it?

448
00:27:45,883 --> 00:27:47,573
How about between two floors?

449
00:27:47,573 --> 00:27:50,643
- Between two floors?
- Between first and second floor stairs?

450
00:27:50,643 --> 00:27:52,663
She brought them to show people?

451
00:27:52,663 --> 00:27:54,683
I'll take out mine when I unpack later.

452
00:27:54,683 --> 00:27:56,073
Sounds good.

453
00:27:56,073 --> 00:27:58,993
I tried it on in the room earlier.

454
00:27:58,993 --> 00:28:00,863
It's pretty.

455
00:28:02,273 --> 00:28:04,343
I was so jealous.

456
00:28:06,773 --> 00:28:11,643
[Concerned]

457
00:28:11,643 --> 00:28:14,533
She's showing off right now.

458
00:28:16,913 --> 00:28:18,773
[Sigh]

459
00:28:20,573 --> 00:28:22,553
Here?

460
00:28:23,693 --> 00:28:29,193
[Putting the scarf in an awkward spot]

461
00:28:31,433 --> 00:28:33,093
Daebak.

462
00:28:35,853 --> 00:28:39,433
Isn't it a bit chilly in here?

463
00:28:39,433 --> 00:28:41,063
- A little.
- Right?

464
00:28:41,063 --> 00:28:45,023
- It hasn't reached the temperature yet.
- I know.

465
00:28:48,493 --> 00:28:51,523
Should we go to a bookstore after the movie?

466
00:28:51,523 --> 00:28:54,043
- Sounds good.
- Get books...

467
00:28:54,043 --> 00:28:56,713
Let's get books to read here.

468
00:28:58,963 --> 00:29:01,593
And we'll eat. Should we eat first?

469
00:29:01,593 --> 00:29:02,813
Yes.

470
00:29:02,813 --> 00:29:05,943
Should we eat first and go to the movie?

471
00:29:05,943 --> 00:29:06,703
Yes.

472
00:29:06,703 --> 00:29:09,903
Should we go to a cafe and to the bookstore?

473
00:29:12,643 --> 00:29:14,593
[Sigh]

474
00:29:14,593 --> 00:29:17,193
- What's up?
- Why?

475
00:29:17,193 --> 00:29:18,913
It's weird.

476
00:29:20,463 --> 00:29:23,913
So Yun is feeling abandoned right now.

477
00:29:25,463 --> 00:29:27,073
Let's do it here.

478
00:29:27,073 --> 00:29:29,583
[Their time in Japan]

479
00:29:29,583 --> 00:29:31,953
- I love it.
- So pretty.

480
00:29:31,953 --> 00:29:34,263
[Their time in Japan]

481
00:29:36,243 --> 00:29:38,943
Her feelings are clear.

482
00:29:38,943 --> 00:29:42,523
[Looking at the photos they took]

483
00:29:42,523 --> 00:29:47,603
[But she's starting to feel]

484
00:29:47,603 --> 00:29:51,973
[a distance between them]

485
00:29:53,333 --> 00:29:54,113
[Head down]

486
00:29:54,113 --> 00:29:56,173
My gosh.

487
00:29:58,873 --> 00:29:59,693
[Glancing]

488
00:30:01,893 --> 00:30:05,553
- Are you not feeling well?
- No, why?

489
00:30:05,553 --> 00:30:07,393
I was just asking.

490
00:30:15,553 --> 00:30:20,663
[She started feeling anxious at some point]

491
00:30:20,663 --> 00:30:24,583
No, no. Someone will eat that at night.

492
00:30:30,483 --> 00:30:35,893
[Leaving the room again]

493
00:30:35,893 --> 00:30:38,463
- I'll have one.
- Let's have one each.

494
00:30:38,463 --> 00:30:40,843
Should we use this? Something bigger, right?

495
00:30:40,843 --> 00:30:43,223
- What are you doing secretly?
- My goodness.

496
00:30:43,223 --> 00:30:46,203
- We're making ramen.
- Ramen?

497
00:30:46,203 --> 00:30:48,013
Let's have ramen.

498
00:30:48,013 --> 00:30:51,373
Do you use filtered water?

499
00:30:51,373 --> 00:30:54,373
Use this. I was going to upgrade it.

500
00:30:54,373 --> 00:30:57,773
- I make amazing ramen.
- Really?

501
00:30:57,773 --> 00:31:01,463
I have a trauma about it. So...

502
00:31:03,513 --> 00:31:05,873
- They're making ramen. Who wants it?
- Really?

503
00:31:05,873 --> 00:31:08,843
- I want to cook, too.
- I'm okay.

504
00:31:08,843 --> 00:31:10,913
- Was it two?
- Yes.

505
00:31:10,913 --> 00:31:13,523
They're coming this way.

506
00:31:13,523 --> 00:31:15,953
- Ramen?
- She brought people over.

507
00:31:15,953 --> 00:31:18,053
- Who wants it?
- I think five is enough.

508
00:31:18,053 --> 00:31:20,143
Five. Sounds good.

509
00:31:20,143 --> 00:31:23,433
Everyone will have some once they smell it.

510
00:31:23,433 --> 00:31:26,043
The water amount is for one serving.

511
00:31:26,043 --> 00:31:28,773
For five servings, it's 2.5 liters.

512
00:31:35,883 --> 00:31:40,163
- It's up to the chef.
- The pot is strange.

513
00:31:40,163 --> 00:31:42,913
Seo Won is good at making it.

514
00:31:42,913 --> 00:31:45,063
C-Can I do it?

515
00:31:45,063 --> 00:31:46,803
Yes, go ahead.

516
00:31:46,803 --> 00:31:49,403
Should someone make Chapagetti,
and the other make cup ramen?

517
00:31:49,403 --> 00:31:52,243
- Let's do it together.
- Yes, let's.

518
00:31:52,243 --> 00:31:54,553
I'll make cup ramen, then.

519
00:31:54,553 --> 00:31:58,253
Why? Are you not confident?
I'll do it. I'll do it.

520
00:31:58,253 --> 00:32:00,283
- Rest in the living room.
- Really?

521
00:32:00,283 --> 00:32:02,173
Of course. Leave it to us.

522
00:32:02,173 --> 00:32:04,233
- Thank you.
- I'll leave you to it.

523
00:32:04,233 --> 00:32:06,743
She's changing things up.

524
00:32:06,743 --> 00:32:09,393
You have to cook the broth first.

525
00:32:09,393 --> 00:32:14,073
[Friendship brewing in the kitchen]

526
00:32:15,973 --> 00:32:18,553
- What are you guys doing tomorrow?
- Gosh...

527
00:32:18,553 --> 00:32:21,113
I think I'll go out tomorrow.

528
00:32:21,113 --> 00:32:22,673
Where?

529
00:32:24,443 --> 00:32:27,363
- I have...
- So uncomfortable.

530
00:32:27,363 --> 00:32:29,793
- I have a plan.
- Plan?

531
00:32:29,793 --> 00:32:31,783
So uncomfortable.

532
00:32:32,813 --> 00:32:36,673
- How awkward.
- She can't brag about it.

533
00:32:36,673 --> 00:32:38,663
I need milk.

534
00:32:42,063 --> 00:32:46,593
[They looked extra close]

535
00:33:00,013 --> 00:33:04,243
[Anxiety is growing tonight]

536
00:33:04,243 --> 00:33:05,543
Oh, my gosh.

537
00:33:05,543 --> 00:33:07,513
It looks like just another night,

538
00:33:07,513 --> 00:33:10,053
but there was a lot of drama.

539
00:33:10,053 --> 00:33:14,383
It's the night they returned from the trip.

540
00:33:14,383 --> 00:33:19,113
So much drama happened in just one night.

541
00:33:19,113 --> 00:33:21,513
Gyu Ri could've made the move first.

542
00:33:21,513 --> 00:33:24,213
But Yu Gyeong was the one
who made the move first.

543
00:33:24,213 --> 00:33:28,713
- This could work out well for her later on.
- Totally.

544
00:33:28,713 --> 00:33:31,243
If she were the second or
third one to make a move,

545
00:33:31,243 --> 00:33:33,733
she could've ended up alone tomorrow.

546
00:33:33,733 --> 00:33:36,333
You have to make the first move.
That's the way to go.

547
00:33:36,333 --> 00:33:39,073
Especially in this environment,
on Heart Signal.

548
00:33:39,073 --> 00:33:43,023
- So crazy. So Yun is upset, too.
- So crazy.

549
00:33:43,023 --> 00:33:46,373
[The morning has come]

550
00:33:46,373 --> 00:33:49,763
[Seo Won is leaving the house first]

551
00:33:51,643 --> 00:33:57,243
[Starting the day, feeling relaxed]

552
00:34:03,163 --> 00:34:06,303
[It's a bit past lunchtime]

553
00:34:06,933 --> 00:34:09,783
[Wu Yeol is getting ready to go out]

554
00:34:10,503 --> 00:34:11,813
[And Yu Gyeong came to see him]

555
00:34:11,813 --> 00:34:13,843
What time should we leave?

556
00:34:13,843 --> 00:34:15,853
Let's leave after four.

557
00:34:15,853 --> 00:34:17,913
Okay, got it.

558
00:34:17,913 --> 00:34:20,483
- Did you eat?
- No, I didn't.

559
00:34:20,483 --> 00:34:23,693
Let's eat, then. Should we eat downstairs?

560
00:34:23,693 --> 00:34:28,913
[Scanning the fridge]

561
00:34:28,913 --> 00:34:32,263
[Decided to have yogurt today]

562
00:34:32,263 --> 00:34:34,713
You slept so soundly.

563
00:34:34,713 --> 00:34:37,823
My face is puffy
because I had ramen last night.

564
00:34:37,823 --> 00:34:40,103
It looks a little puffy.

565
00:34:41,293 --> 00:34:44,043
- You're good at this.
- Do you want this?

566
00:34:44,043 --> 00:34:46,643
How did you peel it like that?

567
00:34:47,913 --> 00:34:50,993
I don't lick the lid.

568
00:34:50,993 --> 00:34:52,533
[Laughing]

569
00:34:52,533 --> 00:34:54,493
That's why I scrape it like this.

570
00:34:54,493 --> 00:34:58,013
I'll have about a third of a bowl.

571
00:34:58,013 --> 00:35:01,263
[Adding toppings to their liking]

572
00:35:01,263 --> 00:35:03,823
We'll be eating like this forever.

573
00:35:04,793 --> 00:35:06,313
[Yum]

574
00:35:08,263 --> 00:35:10,523
I feel healthier now.

575
00:35:11,993 --> 00:35:13,083
[Yum]

576
00:35:14,233 --> 00:35:18,263
I don't have to eat anything after this.

577
00:35:19,053 --> 00:35:21,833
I need to lose weight.

578
00:35:21,833 --> 00:35:23,643
Why would you lose weight?

579
00:35:23,643 --> 00:35:25,673
I have to.

580
00:35:25,673 --> 00:35:28,473
No, you'll pass out.

581
00:35:28,473 --> 00:35:31,473
[That comment makes her laugh]

582
00:35:35,293 --> 00:35:39,703
[It feels like it will be a pleasant day]

583
00:35:43,743 --> 00:35:46,583
[Humming]

584
00:35:53,013 --> 00:35:54,903
[Smiling]

585
00:35:54,903 --> 00:35:58,583
- Hi.
- Huh? She looks happy.

586
00:35:59,493 --> 00:36:02,493
- Hi.
- Hi.

587
00:36:02,493 --> 00:36:04,383
- Wow.
- You look so pretty.

588
00:36:04,383 --> 00:36:06,763
- Did the move go well?
- Yes.

589
00:36:06,763 --> 00:36:09,273
I look fine, right? Do I look tired?

590
00:36:09,273 --> 00:36:11,673
- No, you look fine.
- I'm glad to hear that.

591
00:36:11,673 --> 00:36:13,553
- You must be tired.
- No, I'm okay.

592
00:36:13,553 --> 00:36:15,893
- Really?
- Yes.

593
00:36:15,893 --> 00:36:17,753
That's a black coat.

594
00:36:17,753 --> 00:36:19,393
- I've never seen that before.
- It's navy.

595
00:36:19,393 --> 00:36:20,943
Is it navy? I've never seen it.

596
00:36:20,943 --> 00:36:22,633
Gosh, he has a good memory.

597
00:36:22,633 --> 00:36:25,323
I chose this outfit very carefully.

598
00:36:25,323 --> 00:36:27,393
I worked very hard on it.

599
00:36:27,393 --> 00:36:30,783
I'm wearing an olive-colored skirt, too.

600
00:36:31,633 --> 00:36:33,583
You look so pretty.

601
00:36:33,583 --> 00:36:38,113
She never showed
that much enthusiasm for him.

602
00:36:38,113 --> 00:36:39,153
You look cool.

603
00:36:39,153 --> 00:36:41,153
[Looking]

604
00:36:41,153 --> 00:36:44,813
- He's flustered.
- Was it warm enough?

605
00:36:48,263 --> 00:36:50,463
[Busy fingers under the table]

606
00:36:50,463 --> 00:36:52,913
He's shy. He's shy.

607
00:36:52,913 --> 00:36:54,323
[Gulp]

608
00:36:54,323 --> 00:36:56,083
I'm excited.

609
00:36:56,083 --> 00:36:58,783
- Excited for the movie, right?
- Yes.

610
00:36:58,783 --> 00:37:00,303
How are we watching the movie?

611
00:37:00,303 --> 00:37:02,623
The movie? I bought the tickets.

612
00:37:02,623 --> 00:37:06,533
I chose the time, seats, and location myself.

613
00:37:06,533 --> 00:37:08,783
When? What time?

614
00:37:08,783 --> 00:37:10,923
- What time is it now?
- 4:06.

615
00:37:10,923 --> 00:37:14,073
- 5:20.
- That's perfect.

616
00:37:14,073 --> 00:37:17,723
How did you choose the perfect time?

617
00:37:17,723 --> 00:37:20,123
I bought the tickets last night
at the last minute.

618
00:37:20,123 --> 00:37:22,663
I wanted to get good seats.

619
00:37:22,663 --> 00:37:25,813
So, I got the middle F-row seats.

620
00:37:25,813 --> 00:37:28,963
There will be people around us,
unfortunately.

621
00:37:28,963 --> 00:37:30,943
- It just can't be the front row.
- Right.

622
00:37:30,943 --> 00:37:32,403
You have to watch like this.

623
00:37:32,403 --> 00:37:36,293
- You can't watch that movie like this.
- Right, right.

624
00:37:36,293 --> 00:37:39,773
That's why I chose that location.

625
00:37:39,773 --> 00:37:42,033
I'm looking forward to it.

626
00:37:42,973 --> 00:37:45,253
Don't look forward to it.

627
00:37:45,253 --> 00:37:49,253
[Excited]

628
00:37:49,253 --> 00:37:51,963
The Fashion Week keeps popping up on my feed.

629
00:37:51,963 --> 00:37:53,543
[Pause]

630
00:37:53,543 --> 00:37:55,253
- Did you see it?
- Yes.

631
00:37:55,253 --> 00:37:56,793
- Everything?
- Yes.

632
00:37:56,793 --> 00:37:59,823
- It's all over my feed right now.
- Really?

633
00:37:59,823 --> 00:38:02,053
I recognized you immediately.

634
00:38:02,053 --> 00:38:03,663
So cute.

635
00:38:03,663 --> 00:38:06,323
You caught my attention immediately.

636
00:38:07,493 --> 00:38:10,553
- It was crazy.
- Her energy is different today.

637
00:38:11,983 --> 00:38:16,013
[The first dish has arrived]

638
00:38:16,013 --> 00:38:18,643
- Yes.
- Thank you.

639
00:38:18,643 --> 00:38:19,873
[Slipping]

640
00:38:19,873 --> 00:38:22,553
[The tomato is hard to cut]

641
00:38:22,553 --> 00:38:24,363
[Laughing]

642
00:38:25,963 --> 00:38:28,843
Is that for me?

643
00:38:28,843 --> 00:38:30,273
Thank you.

644
00:38:30,273 --> 00:38:32,043
I'm sorry it's not so pretty.

645
00:38:32,043 --> 00:38:33,443
Thank you.

646
00:38:33,443 --> 00:38:35,273
[Yum]

647
00:38:35,803 --> 00:38:38,123
[Mmm]

648
00:38:38,123 --> 00:38:39,393
Right?

649
00:38:39,393 --> 00:38:41,103
Let's eat the whole thing.

650
00:38:45,183 --> 00:38:48,443
Good-looking people always eat Italian food.

651
00:38:48,443 --> 00:38:51,333
[They can't stop eating]

652
00:38:51,333 --> 00:38:53,343
I'll finish quickly.

653
00:38:55,103 --> 00:38:56,753
[Tasty]

654
00:38:57,823 --> 00:38:59,983
Eat slowly. Slowly.

655
00:39:04,523 --> 00:39:08,383
I'll lose all of my appetite
when I'm home later.

656
00:39:08,383 --> 00:39:10,213
No.

657
00:39:10,213 --> 00:39:13,203
Why? Why?

658
00:39:14,503 --> 00:39:16,283
She's so honest.

659
00:39:16,283 --> 00:39:18,333
I feel nervous every night.

660
00:39:18,333 --> 00:39:20,903
That's a meaningful comment.

661
00:39:22,573 --> 00:39:27,273
[Complicated feelings flooded in last night]

662
00:39:34,303 --> 00:39:35,973
[Socks from Japan]

663
00:39:35,973 --> 00:39:36,943
Thank you.

664
00:39:36,943 --> 00:39:38,503
[Glancing]

665
00:39:38,503 --> 00:39:42,603
- What was that?
- I told him to make sure to wear them.

666
00:39:44,483 --> 00:39:47,423
What are these? Socks? So cute.

667
00:39:47,423 --> 00:39:49,513
- What a nice color.
- I know, right?

668
00:39:49,513 --> 00:39:51,893
They will go well with a gray skirt.

669
00:39:51,893 --> 00:39:53,633
Wow, you're right.

670
00:39:53,633 --> 00:39:55,683
Did you buy them with everyone?

671
00:39:55,683 --> 00:39:57,303
During the first...

672
00:39:57,303 --> 00:39:59,993
- During the date?
- Yes, during the date.

673
00:40:05,643 --> 00:40:10,223
The times I ate well at the house

674
00:40:10,223 --> 00:40:13,083
happened to be when you cooked.

675
00:40:13,083 --> 00:40:15,843
Right. Seo Won was always the reason.

676
00:40:15,843 --> 00:40:19,793
Cooking... I think I can get into it.

677
00:40:19,793 --> 00:40:21,633
It's fun.

678
00:40:21,633 --> 00:40:24,733
Nothing makes me happier
than eating good food.

679
00:40:24,733 --> 00:40:29,143
- My worries are all gone now.
- Puts me in a good mood.

680
00:40:33,803 --> 00:40:35,523
Thank you.

681
00:40:35,523 --> 00:40:40,883
Seo Won might wonder why she's
more relaxed with him.

682
00:40:41,783 --> 00:40:42,413
[Glancing]

683
00:40:45,543 --> 00:40:50,903
[A brief moment of silence]

684
00:40:50,903 --> 00:40:52,813
Do you like eating during a movie?

685
00:40:52,813 --> 00:40:54,253
I do.

686
00:40:55,183 --> 00:40:56,933
We have to get popcorn.

687
00:40:56,933 --> 00:41:01,963
If you want caramel popcorn,
we have to get half and half.

688
00:41:01,963 --> 00:41:04,003
I always get the onion popcorn.

689
00:41:06,923 --> 00:41:09,663
I can't do onion tonight.

690
00:41:10,533 --> 00:41:13,363
I like how decisive you are.

691
00:41:13,363 --> 00:41:14,793
You're cool.

692
00:41:14,793 --> 00:41:18,413
Do you think you'll cry during the movie?

693
00:41:18,413 --> 00:41:20,083
I don't think it'd be sad.

694
00:41:20,083 --> 00:41:22,523
Isn't it just romance?

695
00:41:23,893 --> 00:41:26,773
- The sunshine.
- It's nice.

696
00:41:26,773 --> 00:41:29,833
- How perfect.
- It's perfect.

697
00:41:29,833 --> 00:41:33,193
- I pretty much feel recharged now.
- Me, too.

698
00:41:34,443 --> 00:41:36,923
I'm worried since you struggle to sleep
the most.

699
00:41:36,923 --> 00:41:39,223
You haven't been sleeping.

700
00:41:39,223 --> 00:41:41,023
I'm impressed.

701
00:41:44,573 --> 00:41:46,053
[Checking her face]

702
00:41:46,053 --> 00:41:47,813
So cute.

703
00:41:49,243 --> 00:41:51,323
He's subtly caring.

704
00:41:52,043 --> 00:41:55,863
[The sky turned orange from the sunset]

705
00:41:55,863 --> 00:41:58,313
Since when have you lived alone in Seoul?

706
00:41:58,313 --> 00:41:59,443
- Me?
- Yes.

707
00:41:59,443 --> 00:42:01,543
I moved in February, the year I turned 20.

708
00:42:01,543 --> 00:42:03,453
I signed with the agency in April.

709
00:42:03,453 --> 00:42:05,853
I've worked since,
and then I joined the army.

710
00:42:05,853 --> 00:42:08,103
- The same agency all this time?
- That's right.

711
00:42:08,103 --> 00:42:11,253
That's amazing. You're so loyal.

712
00:42:11,253 --> 00:42:16,633
It'd feel weird to see you
on a billboard later.

713
00:42:17,523 --> 00:42:21,463
I've been wanting to get a book
recommendation from you.

714
00:42:21,463 --> 00:42:25,933
- Book recommendation?
- Yes, you seem so devoted.

715
00:42:25,933 --> 00:42:27,493
Right.

716
00:42:29,473 --> 00:42:31,593
- Really?
- Yes.

717
00:42:33,893 --> 00:42:35,623
- The sun is nice.
- Yes.

718
00:42:39,353 --> 00:42:47,463
I can't remember
how my feelings have changed.

719
00:42:47,463 --> 00:42:49,293
It happens quickly.

720
00:42:50,483 --> 00:42:55,313
A viral disease is going around in the house.

721
00:42:55,313 --> 00:42:57,793
There's a virus going around.

722
00:42:57,793 --> 00:43:03,303
Anyone who moves in there
starts crying a lot.

723
00:43:03,303 --> 00:43:06,033
She's telling him how she feels.

724
00:43:06,833 --> 00:43:10,833
I felt a bit sad
when I was with you in Japan.

725
00:43:10,833 --> 00:43:11,933
You felt sad?

726
00:43:11,933 --> 00:43:15,213
- He's shocked.
- On Saturday? Or Friday?

727
00:43:15,213 --> 00:43:17,033
- Yes.
- When we spent the day together?

728
00:43:17,033 --> 00:43:20,013
- Why were you sad?
- He must feel...

729
00:43:20,013 --> 00:43:22,223
Did I bore you too much?

730
00:43:22,223 --> 00:43:23,773
He's flustered right now.

731
00:43:23,773 --> 00:43:27,993
No. I don't know. I just...

732
00:43:27,993 --> 00:43:28,833
I don't know.

733
00:43:28,833 --> 00:43:30,323
- What?
- What?

734
00:43:30,323 --> 00:43:33,183
You kept playing sad music.

735
00:43:35,433 --> 00:43:38,063
- Sorry.
- That's why.

736
00:43:38,063 --> 00:43:41,463
- You felt sad.
- What's the deal?

737
00:43:41,463 --> 00:43:46,163
Anyway, the place makes you think a lot.

738
00:43:46,163 --> 00:43:48,893
- I know.
- Seriously.

739
00:43:48,893 --> 00:43:51,763
- He has a lot to think about today.
- My gosh.

740
00:43:51,763 --> 00:43:55,043
[He has a lot to think about]

741
00:43:55,043 --> 00:43:59,343
Gosh, he can't just have fun anymore.

742
00:43:59,343 --> 00:44:01,153
Makes us think a lot, too.

743
00:44:01,153 --> 00:44:05,433
I thought
Seo Won seemed serious at first today.

744
00:44:05,433 --> 00:44:08,463
She was like, "I dolled up for our date."

745
00:44:08,463 --> 00:44:10,743
His heart skipped a beat from that.

746
00:44:10,743 --> 00:44:13,713
I thought that was why he got serious.

747
00:44:13,713 --> 00:44:17,533
He thought things would go differently today,

748
00:44:17,533 --> 00:44:20,373
but she said she was sad in Japan,
and he was shocked.

749
00:44:20,373 --> 00:44:22,183
He didn't expect to hear that.

750
00:44:22,183 --> 00:44:25,203
He must understand because he's smart.

751
00:44:25,203 --> 00:44:31,633
She's obviously saying that the cause
of her worries is someone else.

752
00:44:31,633 --> 00:44:34,363
She keeps saying that.

753
00:44:34,363 --> 00:44:35,783
She's telling Seo Won that.

754
00:44:35,783 --> 00:44:39,213
I thought it'd be nice if they
talked about that more.

755
00:44:39,213 --> 00:44:44,843
If he told her how he feels about
her after listening to her,

756
00:44:44,843 --> 00:44:46,523
it could become an opportunity for him.

757
00:44:46,523 --> 00:44:48,133
But how could he tell her?

758
00:44:48,133 --> 00:44:49,753
It's obvious what she would say.

759
00:44:49,753 --> 00:44:52,263
"Wu Yeol doesn't feel the same way I do."

760
00:44:52,263 --> 00:44:54,223
If that's what she meant, it's cruel.

761
00:44:54,223 --> 00:45:00,103
She's not sensitive to Seo Won's feelings.

762
00:45:00,103 --> 00:45:02,253
Because she's too invested in Wu Yeol.

763
00:45:02,253 --> 00:45:06,143
Seo Won must've been curious
as to what she meant,

764
00:45:06,143 --> 00:45:08,253
but he didn't ask more.

765
00:45:08,253 --> 00:45:11,003
- Isn't Seo Won so cool?
- He's the best.

766
00:45:11,003 --> 00:45:13,693
Where can you meet someone like him?

767
00:45:13,693 --> 00:45:16,813
I want to tell him about my worries, too.

768
00:45:16,813 --> 00:45:20,903
All he does is listen. He doesn't argue.

769
00:45:20,903 --> 00:45:22,743
He's amazingly thoughtful.

770
00:45:22,743 --> 00:45:25,803
Come on and notice him.

771
00:45:26,653 --> 00:45:29,333
- We're out of time.
- I know.

772
00:45:29,333 --> 00:45:32,033
We should get the takeout and go right away.

773
00:45:34,023 --> 00:45:35,463
I'm excited.

774
00:45:36,383 --> 00:45:37,793
I'm excited, too.

775
00:45:37,793 --> 00:45:41,093
Wow, so exciting.

776
00:45:42,213 --> 00:45:44,823
I'll play music.

777
00:45:44,823 --> 00:45:46,773
I'll show you.

778
00:45:52,773 --> 00:45:56,253
- They're so happy right now.
- They are.

779
00:46:04,043 --> 00:46:05,353
[Getting all the sun]

780
00:46:05,353 --> 00:46:07,003
Too bright.

781
00:46:09,143 --> 00:46:11,093
Is it too bright?

782
00:46:11,093 --> 00:46:16,053
It's only bothering me because I'm shorter.

783
00:46:18,163 --> 00:46:21,073
[Got pastry for a snack]

784
00:46:21,073 --> 00:46:23,703
- This is insane.
- Really?

785
00:46:23,703 --> 00:46:25,083
It's so insane.

786
00:46:25,083 --> 00:46:26,573
I want some, too.

787
00:46:26,573 --> 00:46:31,213
- Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
- They're sharing it!

788
00:46:36,783 --> 00:46:39,213
- So good.
- Isn't it?

789
00:46:41,923 --> 00:46:44,923
Are they dating? What's the deal?

790
00:46:44,923 --> 00:46:48,203
That means they're really close now.

791
00:46:50,993 --> 00:46:52,473
So exciting. So exciting.

792
00:46:52,473 --> 00:46:57,893
I want to see that. There's a play
version of "Spirited Away."

793
00:46:57,893 --> 00:47:01,633
- Do you want to see it?
- Yes, do you like Ghibli films?

794
00:47:01,633 --> 00:47:06,903
- I've seen one a long time ago.
- "Howl's Moving Castle"?

795
00:47:06,903 --> 00:47:09,473
My friends tell me I look like Howl.

796
00:47:09,473 --> 00:47:13,213
They think I look like a Japanese actor.

797
00:47:14,863 --> 00:47:16,633
I can see that.

798
00:47:18,303 --> 00:47:21,873
I was sad about it,
but you're agreeing with them.

799
00:47:21,873 --> 00:47:24,183
[Cracking up]

800
00:47:25,693 --> 00:47:27,683
It means you're charming.

801
00:47:28,763 --> 00:47:30,193
Okay.

802
00:47:32,353 --> 00:47:34,773
- Tasty, right?
- Wow, seriously.

803
00:47:34,773 --> 00:47:36,413
It's tasty.

804
00:47:36,413 --> 00:47:38,573
Why did you eat the part without cheese?

805
00:47:38,573 --> 00:47:40,803
I wanted you to get the cheese.

806
00:47:41,803 --> 00:47:44,453
We're starting to look alike.

807
00:47:44,453 --> 00:47:49,643
Whenever I talk to you, I unconsciously...

808
00:47:49,643 --> 00:47:53,283
I feel like I keep changing.

809
00:47:53,283 --> 00:47:56,853
People start acting like each other
when they're together.

810
00:47:56,853 --> 00:47:59,313
[Hehe]

811
00:48:00,273 --> 00:48:04,023
[They arrive at the movie theater]

812
00:48:08,093 --> 00:48:11,053
Should we get the tickets first?

813
00:48:14,063 --> 00:48:16,653
Wow, daebak.

814
00:48:18,053 --> 00:48:20,953
We should've been on top of it.

815
00:48:20,953 --> 00:48:23,453
- Let's get Cola.
- Cola? Which one?

816
00:48:23,453 --> 00:48:26,533
The normal kind? You don't drink zero?

817
00:48:29,093 --> 00:48:30,683
Which one do you want?

818
00:48:30,683 --> 00:48:31,873
- The Shin-chan one.
- Shin-chan?

819
00:48:31,873 --> 00:48:33,353
[Leaning]

820
00:48:33,353 --> 00:48:35,163
He feeds her now?

821
00:48:35,163 --> 00:48:38,033
You can enter.
It's Theater 1 on the sixth floor.

822
00:48:38,033 --> 00:48:39,903
Thank you.

823
00:48:42,833 --> 00:48:45,733
- Am I too high up?
- Hold on.

824
00:48:47,503 --> 00:48:49,233
I'll be above you later.

825
00:48:49,233 --> 00:48:51,673
They're standing so close together.

826
00:48:52,663 --> 00:48:55,463
Gosh. Why is he staring at her?

827
00:48:58,873 --> 00:49:02,223
What? Why did you go down two steps?

828
00:49:02,223 --> 00:49:03,363
We're on the same level now.

829
00:49:03,363 --> 00:49:07,083
Every little thing is fun on a real date.

830
00:49:07,083 --> 00:49:09,163
- This is weird.
- Why?

831
00:49:09,163 --> 00:49:11,103
I'm too high up.

832
00:49:12,633 --> 00:49:14,843
This is it, right?

833
00:49:14,843 --> 00:49:16,533
Where are our seats?

834
00:49:16,533 --> 00:49:21,153
[Arrived at the theater]

835
00:49:23,843 --> 00:49:25,713
Our row is after this.

836
00:49:25,713 --> 00:49:27,973
- The back one?
- Yes.

837
00:49:27,973 --> 00:49:29,983
Is it not?

838
00:49:29,983 --> 00:49:33,733
[They're taking the couple's seats]

839
00:49:33,733 --> 00:49:37,303
- They get to sit privately.
- All the way in the back.

840
00:49:40,533 --> 00:49:42,053
This is nice.

841
00:49:42,053 --> 00:49:45,193
Wow, this is a big deal.

842
00:49:45,193 --> 00:49:47,033
Take one like this?

843
00:49:50,053 --> 00:49:51,473
[Click]

844
00:49:51,473 --> 00:49:54,243
Here's the camera.

845
00:49:54,243 --> 00:49:56,083
Together?

846
00:49:58,573 --> 00:50:00,923
- My hands are freezing.
- Mine, too.

847
00:50:00,923 --> 00:50:04,043
- What are they doing?
- They held hands?

848
00:50:09,803 --> 00:50:12,883
So, do you cry while watching sad movies?

849
00:50:12,883 --> 00:50:17,473
Yes, I totally bawl.

850
00:50:18,453 --> 00:50:20,933
But I've been holding it in.

851
00:50:20,933 --> 00:50:23,613
- Is this sad, too?
- Yes.

852
00:50:23,613 --> 00:50:25,983
- Very sad?
- Totally.

853
00:50:25,983 --> 00:50:28,503
- It's a tear-jerker.
- Really?

854
00:50:29,263 --> 00:50:31,653
We aren't late, right?

855
00:50:31,653 --> 00:50:33,453
No way.

856
00:50:33,453 --> 00:50:35,013
Hold on.

857
00:50:36,173 --> 00:50:37,893
The Truman Show?

858
00:50:39,453 --> 00:50:43,293
- What? What? What?
- No way.

859
00:50:43,293 --> 00:50:46,583
We thought we had discovered it.

860
00:50:47,523 --> 00:50:49,773
- Hold on. Hold on.
- Really?

861
00:51:02,673 --> 00:51:03,803
[Coming in]

862
00:51:03,803 --> 00:51:05,903
Should we look for our seats?

863
00:51:06,623 --> 00:51:09,763
[Gyu Ri and Seo Won]

864
00:51:09,763 --> 00:51:12,253
Are they...

865
00:51:12,253 --> 00:51:14,933
- This can't be.
- This can't be real. Seriously.

866
00:51:14,933 --> 00:51:17,493
They won't see each other since it's dark.

867
00:51:17,493 --> 00:51:19,603
But Seo Won sticks out so much.

868
00:51:19,603 --> 00:51:22,643
Row D, E, F...

869
00:51:22,643 --> 00:51:26,153
[Gyu Ri and Seo Won are
entering the same theater]

870
00:51:26,153 --> 00:51:27,753
This is it.

871
00:51:28,453 --> 00:51:30,683
They didn't see them. They didn't.

872
00:51:32,333 --> 00:51:35,453
[They're sitting toward the middle]

873
00:51:35,453 --> 00:51:37,793
The Gangnam location is nice.

874
00:51:39,593 --> 00:51:41,743
Should we do 5:20?

875
00:51:41,743 --> 00:51:44,963
- 5:20.
- That's perfect.

876
00:51:44,963 --> 00:51:49,353
[The four coincidentally
watch the movie together]

877
00:51:49,353 --> 00:51:52,223
- Can you watch that without crying?
- No.

878
00:51:52,223 --> 00:51:54,833
- I think I'll cry.
- I'm already tearing up.

879
00:51:54,833 --> 00:51:56,963
Oh, my gosh!

880
00:51:56,963 --> 00:52:01,433
- This is crazy.
- I'll be crying with my nose running.

881
00:52:01,433 --> 00:52:02,723
I'll wipe your face for you.

882
00:52:02,723 --> 00:52:12,013
[The movie starts without them
noticing each other]

883
00:52:12,013 --> 00:52:15,453
Later? I have a lot.

884
00:52:25,663 --> 00:52:28,903
[Whispering]

885
00:52:32,793 --> 00:52:34,433
Huh? Oh, my gosh!

886
00:52:34,433 --> 00:52:36,903
I thought she was leaning on him.

887
00:52:36,903 --> 00:52:41,453
[Same space]

888
00:52:41,453 --> 00:52:46,863
[Same space, different feelings]

889
00:52:51,243 --> 00:52:59,183
[Things are getting intense]

890
00:53:00,953 --> 00:53:04,063
Seo Won is crying. He's crying.

891
00:53:08,113 --> 00:53:18,113
[This man is crying uncontrollably]

892
00:53:19,623 --> 00:53:23,213
- He's crying hard.
- He should've brought tissues.

893
00:53:23,213 --> 00:53:26,473
- I really like Seo Won.
- Me, too.

894
00:53:26,473 --> 00:53:28,133
Wow...

895
00:53:32,333 --> 00:53:36,403
Gosh, she's crying with her big eyes.

896
00:53:44,823 --> 00:53:48,153
[The movie ended]

897
00:53:52,983 --> 00:53:55,553
Huh? Hey, hey, hey!

898
00:53:55,553 --> 00:53:57,343
I didn't cry.

899
00:53:58,193 --> 00:53:59,683
Did you enjoy it?

900
00:53:59,683 --> 00:54:01,703
- What the heck?
- I can't see!

901
00:54:01,703 --> 00:54:03,573
Why is it so dark?

902
00:54:04,633 --> 00:54:07,273
The music is too much.

903
00:54:10,163 --> 00:54:11,523
[Teary]

904
00:54:11,523 --> 00:54:13,253
So funny.

905
00:54:13,253 --> 00:54:15,653
[Teary]

906
00:54:17,243 --> 00:54:19,283
[Hehe]

907
00:54:19,983 --> 00:54:21,513
I'm dying.

908
00:54:23,493 --> 00:54:24,733
[People are starting to leave]

909
00:54:24,733 --> 00:54:27,083
- Hold on.
- Will they see each other?

910
00:54:30,373 --> 00:54:32,353
All four of them are still seated.

911
00:54:33,883 --> 00:54:35,193
The light came on.

912
00:54:35,193 --> 00:54:36,963
- Let's go.
- Hold on.

913
00:54:36,963 --> 00:54:38,663
Oh, my gosh.

914
00:54:38,663 --> 00:54:40,303
Hold on.

915
00:54:42,923 --> 00:54:45,833
- Wu Yeol saw them.
- He did?

916
00:54:45,833 --> 00:54:47,823
Wu Yeol saw them.

917
00:54:47,823 --> 00:54:50,733
Look at that. What's that?

918
00:54:51,593 --> 00:54:53,493
What?

919
00:54:53,493 --> 00:54:54,973
It's Gyu Ri.

920
00:54:54,973 --> 00:54:57,073
- Where? What are you saying?
- She's in the front.

921
00:54:57,073 --> 00:54:59,333
- Seo Won.
- Let's go.

922
00:54:59,333 --> 00:55:01,593
- Where?
- Over there.

923
00:55:01,593 --> 00:55:04,423
Really? What?

924
00:55:04,423 --> 00:55:06,213
Look at them.

925
00:55:06,213 --> 00:55:08,593
- Seriously?
- Yes.

926
00:55:09,633 --> 00:55:13,673
What? What happened?

927
00:55:13,673 --> 00:55:14,953
[Unbelievable]

928
00:55:14,953 --> 00:55:16,673
How could this be?

929
00:55:18,073 --> 00:55:19,573
Let's let them leave.

930
00:55:19,573 --> 00:55:21,013
"Let them leave," she said.

931
00:55:21,013 --> 00:55:23,603
We're suddenly back to reality.

932
00:55:23,603 --> 00:55:26,123
We're back to reality.

933
00:55:26,943 --> 00:55:29,063
This can't be real.

934
00:55:29,063 --> 00:55:30,953
No way.

935
00:55:32,633 --> 00:55:34,803
What happened?

936
00:55:38,543 --> 00:55:40,353
[Hush]

937
00:55:40,353 --> 00:55:42,873
They're hiding. They're hiding.

938
00:55:42,873 --> 00:55:44,693
I got spooked.

939
00:55:44,693 --> 00:55:46,513
Seriously.

940
00:55:48,193 --> 00:55:50,593
- Take your time.
- I wonder who asked.

941
00:55:50,593 --> 00:55:51,913
[They're watching, holding their breath]

942
00:55:51,913 --> 00:55:54,953
What's going on right now?

943
00:56:01,213 --> 00:56:03,573
[Turning back]

944
00:56:03,573 --> 00:56:05,453
Huh? What?

945
00:56:05,453 --> 00:56:08,683
- Did you know... What?
- What?

946
00:56:08,683 --> 00:56:10,703
- Seriously?
- Did you know?

947
00:56:10,703 --> 00:56:13,903
- I just saw you.
- This can't be true.

948
00:56:17,023 --> 00:56:20,503
I just saw you. What are you doing there?

949
00:56:23,083 --> 00:56:25,273
- Let's go.
- Gyu Ri said, "Let's go."

950
00:56:25,273 --> 00:56:28,303
This can't be real. Seriously.

951
00:56:29,723 --> 00:56:31,683
See you later.

952
00:56:31,683 --> 00:56:33,793
- What?
- Daebak.

953
00:56:33,793 --> 00:56:36,003
[Things got awkward]

954
00:56:36,003 --> 00:56:38,233
- What?
- Gyu Ri can't hide her feelings.

955
00:56:38,233 --> 00:56:40,933
We're in trouble.

956
00:56:40,933 --> 00:56:42,323
Wow.

957
00:56:42,323 --> 00:56:44,793
For your information,

958
00:56:44,793 --> 00:56:48,383
- this wasn't staged at all.
- Explain it to the viewers.

959
00:56:48,383 --> 00:56:53,363
This is what happened,
according to the production team.

960
00:56:53,363 --> 00:56:56,833
Wu Yeol bought tickets
at a theater in Gangnam

961
00:56:56,833 --> 00:56:58,533
and let the production know.

962
00:56:58,533 --> 00:57:01,353
To get permission to film from the theater.

963
00:57:01,353 --> 00:57:03,183
After an hour, at 3 a.m.,

964
00:57:03,183 --> 00:57:06,143
Seo Won bought the tickets
at the same theater

965
00:57:06,143 --> 00:57:09,833
for the same time
and let the production know.

966
00:57:09,833 --> 00:57:14,003
The production thought they were
getting involved if they let them know.

967
00:57:14,003 --> 00:57:19,973
Their movie dates are
coincidental 100% in real life.

968
00:57:19,973 --> 00:57:23,293
This isn't totally impossible.

969
00:57:23,293 --> 00:57:24,843
They live in the same area.

970
00:57:24,843 --> 00:57:29,873
There aren't many options to choose from.

971
00:57:29,873 --> 00:57:32,073
What's the deal?

972
00:57:32,073 --> 00:57:34,383
We're in trouble.

973
00:57:36,503 --> 00:57:39,193
They didn't see me crying, right?

974
00:57:39,193 --> 00:57:41,403
- Of course not.
- I just noticed them.

975
00:57:41,403 --> 00:57:43,303
Because he cried?

976
00:57:44,213 --> 00:57:47,603
- This can't be.
- It's unbelievable.

977
00:57:48,443 --> 00:57:50,923
Gosh, this is no good.

978
00:57:50,923 --> 00:57:53,623
I thought it was our own little escapade.

979
00:57:53,623 --> 00:57:56,543
They did the exact same thing.

980
00:57:56,543 --> 00:57:58,073
This is no good.

981
00:57:58,073 --> 00:57:59,863
That's how Yu Gyeong sees it.

982
00:57:59,863 --> 00:58:02,633
Everyone feels differently about it.

983
00:58:02,633 --> 00:58:04,173
Let's go. Let's go.

984
00:58:07,983 --> 00:58:10,633
Gyu Ri feels conflicted about it.

985
00:58:11,463 --> 00:58:13,903
She's having a headache right now.

986
00:58:13,903 --> 00:58:15,883
Is she crying? Is she?

987
00:58:16,713 --> 00:58:19,673
Wow, she's crying now? In front of Seo Won?

988
00:58:19,673 --> 00:58:20,863
Are you still crying?

989
00:58:20,863 --> 00:58:25,103
I held back my tears earlier.

990
00:58:25,103 --> 00:58:26,833
I can't cry.

991
00:58:29,213 --> 00:58:31,903
- I'm strong.
- Let's go this way.

992
00:58:31,903 --> 00:58:35,113
- Let's go.
- No, that's not why she's crying.

993
00:58:35,113 --> 00:58:37,963
Gyu Ri must feel many emotions.

994
00:58:42,133 --> 00:58:44,343
So cold.

995
00:58:46,363 --> 00:58:49,443
- Yu Gyeong must be bothered.
- Of course, she is.

996
00:58:49,443 --> 00:58:53,093
It's like they got caught
when they did nothing wrong.

997
00:58:55,393 --> 00:58:57,253
I want to hear more.

998
00:58:58,083 --> 00:59:01,143
What did you think? What did you think?

999
00:59:01,143 --> 00:59:02,873
I'll tell you over the meal.

1000
00:59:02,873 --> 00:59:04,743
Or in the car?

1001
00:59:05,723 --> 00:59:09,283
- Do you remember everything?
- The plot?

1002
00:59:09,283 --> 00:59:11,823
About how you felt?

1003
00:59:12,963 --> 00:59:14,093
Of course, I do.

1004
00:59:14,093 --> 00:59:16,093
[Trying to change the subject]

1005
00:59:20,653 --> 00:59:23,843
Everyone feels conflicted, including Wu Yeol.

1006
00:59:33,883 --> 00:59:37,773
I really can't believe it.
How could they be sitting there?

1007
00:59:37,773 --> 00:59:41,373
They aren't talking
about the movie right now.

1008
00:59:56,503 --> 01:00:00,603
- So, aren't you an F type?
- I am.

1009
01:00:01,653 --> 01:00:05,683
I think they both cried. But we...

1010
01:00:05,683 --> 01:00:07,703
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

1011
01:00:07,703 --> 01:00:09,303
That's why...

1012
01:00:17,133 --> 01:00:20,503
Let's do this again
when there's something good.

1013
01:00:20,503 --> 01:00:22,443
Sounds good.

1014
01:00:22,443 --> 01:00:24,503
I'll look up a drive-in theater, too.

1015
01:00:24,503 --> 01:00:26,413
Oh, my.

1016
01:00:29,323 --> 01:00:31,253
That was fun, wasn't it?

1017
01:00:31,253 --> 01:00:35,453
We enjoyed the moment so thoroughly.

1018
01:00:35,453 --> 01:00:37,553
He was totally absorbed.

1019
01:00:38,473 --> 01:00:41,953
Gyu Ri's soul left her body.

1020
01:00:44,173 --> 01:00:47,533
I find the line "It's going to work
out for you" so sad.

1021
01:00:47,533 --> 01:00:49,493
I thought that was so sad.

1022
01:00:49,493 --> 01:00:51,903
What scene did you find memorable?

1023
01:00:51,903 --> 01:00:54,563
I think he's changing the subject for her.

1024
01:00:54,563 --> 01:00:57,483
But Gyu Ri is feeling conflicted.

1025
01:00:57,483 --> 01:00:58,773
[Glancing]

1026
01:00:58,773 --> 01:01:01,313
- What do we do?
- My gosh.

1027
01:01:04,833 --> 01:01:07,503
- I'll start first.
- Okay.

1028
01:01:07,503 --> 01:01:12,693
The female lead's line,
"Thank you for being my home."

1029
01:01:12,693 --> 01:01:15,833
- Right, right.
- It was so relatable.

1030
01:01:15,833 --> 01:01:23,953
I thought dating someone meant
being each other's home.

1031
01:01:30,043 --> 01:01:32,253
It's nice that there's no traffic.

1032
01:01:34,043 --> 01:01:36,263
She can't recover from it.

1033
01:01:41,073 --> 01:01:43,033
[Glancing]

1034
01:01:44,433 --> 01:01:45,973
Your eyes are no longer red.

1035
01:01:45,973 --> 01:01:48,203
Really? Yay.

1036
01:01:49,083 --> 01:01:51,503
- Let me see.
- What?

1037
01:01:52,353 --> 01:01:55,343
I'm feeling good now.

1038
01:02:00,723 --> 01:02:03,723
It was sad earlier.

1039
01:02:03,723 --> 01:02:07,293
I know. Who made this movie?

1040
01:02:07,293 --> 01:02:10,223
I thought it was a masterpiece.

1041
01:02:11,393 --> 01:02:14,263
Didn't the two seem fine, by the way?

1042
01:02:14,263 --> 01:02:16,913
- She keeps bringing them up.
- Are they Ts?

1043
01:02:16,913 --> 01:02:18,723
Wu Yeol is a T.

1044
01:02:18,723 --> 01:02:22,613
- They're both T.
- So cold-hearted.

1045
01:02:23,953 --> 01:02:28,633
[She can't stop thinking about it]

1046
01:02:29,803 --> 01:02:35,093
What if I cry on the way to work tomorrow?

1047
01:02:35,093 --> 01:02:38,173
- Why? Because of the movie?
- Yes.

1048
01:02:38,173 --> 01:02:40,793
I'll get emotional at dawn.

1049
01:02:42,503 --> 01:02:44,403
I know.

1050
01:02:44,403 --> 01:02:49,283
It must be tough since she has
to suppress her feelings.

1051
01:02:49,283 --> 01:02:53,353
The tunnel is uphill. How interesting.

1052
01:02:56,833 --> 01:02:59,433
Thank you for the movie.

1053
01:03:01,883 --> 01:03:03,163
Don't mention it.

1054
01:03:03,163 --> 01:03:05,093
I enjoyed it, too.

1055
01:03:06,003 --> 01:03:07,243
Really.

1056
01:03:07,243 --> 01:03:10,383
- I feel hungry after crying.
- I know.

1057
01:03:11,273 --> 01:03:14,433
- It's so funny.
- Daebak.

1058
01:03:18,093 --> 01:03:23,993
[The moment had a lasting impact]

1059
01:03:23,993 --> 01:03:26,923
Did he have to check if she cried like that?

1060
01:03:26,923 --> 01:03:30,573
- Like this.
- His face was right there.

1061
01:03:30,573 --> 01:03:32,063
What's this angle?

1062
01:03:32,063 --> 01:03:34,193
What did they do in the dark, exactly?

1063
01:03:34,193 --> 01:03:36,113
- Weren't they this close?
- They were.

1064
01:03:36,113 --> 01:03:38,123
There are many things to point out.

1065
01:03:38,123 --> 01:03:40,283
They don't care about the encounter.

1066
01:03:40,283 --> 01:03:42,433
They shared one sandwich.

1067
01:03:42,433 --> 01:03:46,143
"Here's another one. Taste this, too."

1068
01:03:46,143 --> 01:03:49,323
Seriously. What's with those two?

1069
01:03:49,323 --> 01:03:51,083
Tell us what's going on.

1070
01:03:51,083 --> 01:03:53,283
- This means...
- What does this mean?

1071
01:03:53,283 --> 01:03:55,733
They don't care about the movie.

1072
01:03:55,733 --> 01:03:58,073
They just want to be together.

1073
01:03:58,073 --> 01:04:00,233
He's right.

1074
01:04:00,233 --> 01:04:03,923
The movie is sad,
but they love being together.

1075
01:04:03,923 --> 01:04:06,453
Why should they cry when they're so happy?

1076
01:04:06,453 --> 01:04:09,493
The fact that they went
to the theater was important.

1077
01:04:09,493 --> 01:04:10,933
You're right.

1078
01:04:10,933 --> 01:04:15,163
Wu Yeol will probably flirt with
someone else at home later...

1079
01:04:15,163 --> 01:04:17,433
- Let's see what happens.
- Am I going too far?

1080
01:04:17,433 --> 01:04:20,053
Sang Min is like this because

1081
01:04:20,053 --> 01:04:24,183
Roy is running wild out of excitement.

1082
01:04:24,183 --> 01:04:26,573
You're like a wild horse right now.

1083
01:04:26,573 --> 01:04:28,113
We got another Lee Sang Min.

1084
01:04:28,113 --> 01:04:29,153
[Can't argue]

1085
01:04:29,153 --> 01:04:31,453
We got a young Lee Sang Min.

1086
01:04:31,453 --> 01:04:36,083
Let's see what happens. We can't
forgive him if that happens.

1087
01:04:36,083 --> 01:04:39,693
Wasn't that more dramatic than the movie?

1088
01:04:39,693 --> 01:04:44,513
They went to see a movie,
but so did the other couple.

1089
01:04:44,513 --> 01:04:47,093
And they have feelings for one another.

1090
01:04:47,093 --> 01:04:50,583
All of this showed in their expressions.

1091
01:04:50,583 --> 01:04:53,463
At the end, after they left,

1092
01:04:53,463 --> 01:04:58,653
Gyu Ri started crying while
going down the escalator.

1093
01:04:58,653 --> 01:05:00,113
That wasn't because of the movie.

1094
01:05:00,113 --> 01:05:01,933
- It wasn't.
- I didn't think so, either.

1095
01:05:01,933 --> 01:05:04,163
It's the feelings she described in the car.

1096
01:05:04,163 --> 01:05:05,453
The sad feelings.

1097
01:05:05,453 --> 01:05:08,613
Heart Signal is so sad. She felt that again.

1098
01:05:08,613 --> 01:05:12,743
Gyu Ri said she wanted to see that movie,

1099
01:05:12,743 --> 01:05:14,133
but Wu Yeol went with Yu Gyeong.

1100
01:05:14,133 --> 01:05:16,823
I think Gyu Ri might feel this way.

1101
01:05:16,823 --> 01:05:21,653
It's not simply that she can't have Wu Yeol.

1102
01:05:21,653 --> 01:05:25,243
She can't like someone who likes her.

1103
01:05:25,243 --> 01:05:27,883
She feels sad because of all that.

1104
01:05:27,883 --> 01:05:30,633
Right. It's so upsetting.

1105
01:05:30,633 --> 01:05:35,243
[After the movie]

1106
01:05:35,243 --> 01:05:37,593
How many servings will you eat?

1107
01:05:37,593 --> 01:05:40,083
18 servings.

1108
01:05:40,083 --> 01:05:41,713
You aren't joking.

1109
01:05:41,713 --> 01:05:43,353
[Heading to eat with all the excitement]

1110
01:05:46,003 --> 01:05:47,603
This is it, right?

1111
01:05:48,463 --> 01:05:52,633
[The long-awaited barbecue date]

1112
01:05:54,633 --> 01:05:57,043
Wow, this place is amazing.

1113
01:05:57,043 --> 01:06:00,523
You like pork skirt, right?

1114
01:06:00,523 --> 01:06:02,313
I do.

1115
01:06:02,313 --> 01:06:05,163
- Pork belly and skirt combo?
- Get the combo?

1116
01:06:05,163 --> 01:06:07,463
- Soybean stew?
- Yes.

1117
01:06:07,463 --> 01:06:08,923
Soju?

1118
01:06:09,923 --> 01:06:11,823
- Somaek?
- Somaek?

1119
01:06:11,823 --> 01:06:15,533
I think soju would get me drunk quickly.

1120
01:06:15,533 --> 01:06:17,043
Let's get somaek.

1121
01:06:17,043 --> 01:06:21,783
We'll have the pork belly and skirt combo,

1122
01:06:21,783 --> 01:06:23,083
soybean stew...

1123
01:06:23,083 --> 01:06:25,973
[Setting the table while Wu Yeol is ordering]

1124
01:06:28,973 --> 01:06:30,293
Should I add this?

1125
01:06:30,293 --> 01:06:32,043
Yes.

1126
01:06:32,043 --> 01:06:33,673
I love it.

1127
01:06:36,163 --> 01:06:38,423
Thank you.

1128
01:06:38,423 --> 01:06:39,393
[Hehe]

1129
01:06:40,293 --> 01:06:42,353
What ratio do you like?

1130
01:06:42,353 --> 01:06:43,923
Me? I don't care.

1131
01:06:43,923 --> 01:06:45,793
- Should I give you more, then?
- Yes.

1132
01:06:45,793 --> 01:06:49,133
- I added just a bit of soju, just in case.
- Sounds good.

1133
01:06:49,133 --> 01:06:50,813
Thank you.

1134
01:06:52,133 --> 01:06:53,123
[Smile]

1135
01:06:54,353 --> 01:06:57,233
- It smells amazing.
- Pork skirt looks tasty.

1136
01:06:57,233 --> 01:06:58,783
I can't wait.

1137
01:06:58,783 --> 01:07:00,513
Seriously.

1138
01:07:02,123 --> 01:07:03,993
Should we take a photo of this?

1139
01:07:03,993 --> 01:07:05,723
How?

1140
01:07:05,723 --> 01:07:07,263
Should we take one of each other?

1141
01:07:07,263 --> 01:07:08,923
[Pause]

1142
01:07:08,923 --> 01:07:12,833
- Do you not want to?
- I do. I'll take one.

1143
01:07:12,833 --> 01:07:15,033
[Snap/Awkward]

1144
01:07:15,033 --> 01:07:18,203
- I can't do it.
- Me, neither.

1145
01:07:18,203 --> 01:07:21,043
I can't do it. What do I do? I can't.

1146
01:07:21,043 --> 01:07:23,663
Raise the glass to the camera.

1147
01:07:23,663 --> 01:07:25,283
Cheers.

1148
01:07:25,283 --> 01:07:27,373
[Raising the glass to the camera]

1149
01:07:27,373 --> 01:07:29,183
What do you think?

1150
01:07:29,183 --> 01:07:30,703
You look cute.

1151
01:07:32,923 --> 01:07:34,863
Daebak.

1152
01:07:34,863 --> 01:07:36,153
They're more natural now.

1153
01:07:36,153 --> 01:07:38,703
Wu Yeol is always natural one-on-one.

1154
01:07:38,703 --> 01:07:41,083
No, this is a bit different.

1155
01:07:41,083 --> 01:07:45,753
He felt seasoned before,
but now he's natural.

1156
01:07:45,753 --> 01:07:48,333
They feel like friends now.

1157
01:07:49,553 --> 01:07:51,843
It's so good.

1158
01:07:53,593 --> 01:07:56,283
Aren't you glad we're eating meat?

1159
01:07:56,283 --> 01:07:58,373
I was craving meat.

1160
01:07:59,693 --> 01:08:03,253
It's nice that we're following
our plan, isn't it?

1161
01:08:03,253 --> 01:08:05,573
We saw a movie, too.

1162
01:08:05,573 --> 01:08:08,153
We're eating meat,
and we got two popcorn flavors.

1163
01:08:08,153 --> 01:08:09,623
Right.

1164
01:08:09,623 --> 01:08:11,293
So pretty.

1165
01:08:11,293 --> 01:08:15,093
I was happy that
you suggested seeing the movie.

1166
01:08:15,093 --> 01:08:17,443
[Last night]

1167
01:08:17,443 --> 01:08:19,163
Tomorrow?

1168
01:08:19,163 --> 01:08:20,743
Want to see a movie?

1169
01:08:22,933 --> 01:08:26,903
With a blank expression, you said,

1170
01:08:26,903 --> 01:08:29,403
"Movie? Let's go."

1171
01:08:29,403 --> 01:08:32,803
So, I was like, "Does he want to or not?"

1172
01:08:32,803 --> 01:08:34,243
Right, right.

1173
01:08:34,243 --> 01:08:36,593
I was suggesting that we go.

1174
01:08:36,593 --> 01:08:38,403
I wouldn't have if I didn't want to.

1175
01:08:38,403 --> 01:08:41,753
- That's how Wu Yeol is.
- Gosh.

1176
01:08:41,753 --> 01:08:43,323
Should we clank our glasses?

1177
01:08:44,943 --> 01:08:45,983
[Clank]

1178
01:08:54,493 --> 01:08:56,153
Call the police.

1179
01:08:59,043 --> 01:09:01,333
I want to do this after work every day.

1180
01:09:02,523 --> 01:09:06,003
You want to have pork and soju
every day after work?

1181
01:09:06,003 --> 01:09:09,153
- Eat tasty food together.
- Really?

1182
01:09:09,153 --> 01:09:12,183
I want us to spend more time outside.

1183
01:09:12,183 --> 01:09:13,683
Really?

1184
01:09:14,733 --> 01:09:16,613
It's really nice.

1185
01:09:18,093 --> 01:09:21,413
This is the most fun thing I've done here.

1186
01:09:21,413 --> 01:09:23,553
- Really?
- Having pork and soju.

1187
01:09:24,643 --> 01:09:29,153
- What?
- She gets afraid when he's forward.

1188
01:09:29,153 --> 01:09:31,853
You're happy that it's tasty, right?

1189
01:09:31,853 --> 01:09:34,293
No, it's because we're together.

1190
01:09:34,293 --> 01:09:36,143
Why are you being so negative?

1191
01:09:36,143 --> 01:09:39,663
- I know.
- Do you think I'm...

1192
01:09:39,663 --> 01:09:41,833
Do you think I'm not...

1193
01:09:41,833 --> 01:09:44,143
[Glancing]

1194
01:09:45,683 --> 01:09:47,493
Do I not seem that way?

1195
01:09:47,493 --> 01:09:50,533
- Hey, buddy.
- Of course, she doubts you.

1196
01:09:50,533 --> 01:09:52,923
We understand Yu Gyeong.

1197
01:09:55,153 --> 01:09:57,613
Tell him. Tell him, please.

1198
01:09:57,613 --> 01:10:02,423
I'm very happy right now, but I think...

1199
01:10:02,423 --> 01:10:07,863
- I keep doubting you?
- You're like, "You meant this, right?"

1200
01:10:07,863 --> 01:10:13,183
I wonder if I made you feel that way.

1201
01:10:13,183 --> 01:10:17,023
He's being more open about his feelings.

1202
01:10:22,943 --> 01:10:23,673
[Glancing]

1203
01:10:29,853 --> 01:10:31,693
You know...

1204
01:10:35,763 --> 01:10:39,973
I feel like I don't know
what you're thinking.

1205
01:10:41,383 --> 01:10:46,723
- Like which direction you're heading.
- Really?

1206
01:10:47,683 --> 01:10:48,773
[Staring]

1207
01:10:48,773 --> 01:10:50,223
- Good job.
- She's talking.

1208
01:10:50,223 --> 01:10:52,543
That's very Yu Gyeong. Good job.

1209
01:10:53,833 --> 01:10:55,503
[Looking]

1210
01:10:57,033 --> 01:11:00,813
Is it because I don't really express myself?

1211
01:11:02,883 --> 01:11:05,593
You said last time...

1212
01:11:06,543 --> 01:11:09,003
that you tend to make the first move.

1213
01:11:09,003 --> 01:11:13,173
And that you make it clear
when you like someone.

1214
01:11:13,173 --> 01:11:16,693
- Yu Gyeong is so good.
- I know. Good job.

1215
01:11:18,693 --> 01:11:24,573
I can sense that
you're not expressing yourself,

1216
01:11:24,573 --> 01:11:30,893
so it makes me hold back from you.

1217
01:11:32,403 --> 01:11:36,023
[Yu Gyeong courageously
brings up her feelings]

1218
01:11:38,763 --> 01:11:41,143
But I'm not saying this because...

1219
01:11:42,043 --> 01:11:45,673
I think you obviously like me,
or something like that.

1220
01:11:45,673 --> 01:11:47,863
Of course.

1221
01:11:53,923 --> 01:11:55,453
[Debating]

1222
01:11:55,453 --> 01:11:56,763
He can't give her a clear answer.

1223
01:11:56,763 --> 01:11:59,273
- Just wait.
- Wait.

1224
01:12:03,093 --> 01:12:05,143
How do I express this?

1225
01:12:12,143 --> 01:12:16,603
A bunch of things
have been bothering me lately.

1226
01:12:19,633 --> 01:12:22,653
We were really good at the beginning,

1227
01:12:22,653 --> 01:12:27,343
but we didn't have
that many chances to interact.

1228
01:12:27,343 --> 01:12:30,243
Conversations and such...

1229
01:12:30,243 --> 01:12:34,813
- I was a little upset.
- He's been feeling it, too.

1230
01:12:39,003 --> 01:12:41,553
[Hesitating]

1231
01:12:49,013 --> 01:12:53,593
[Did he not have the courage
to express his feelings?]

1232
01:12:55,193 --> 01:12:57,213
I was a little upset.

1233
01:12:59,693 --> 01:13:02,723
- And, and?
- And?

1234
01:13:02,723 --> 01:13:06,303
I know I was pretty down.

1235
01:13:08,773 --> 01:13:13,893
I know you were struggling, too.

1236
01:13:15,183 --> 01:13:17,833
I didn't know how to face you.

1237
01:13:21,043 --> 01:13:23,523
[Staring]

1238
01:13:26,273 --> 01:13:28,333
Inside...

1239
01:13:30,363 --> 01:13:32,833
I had a lot on my mind.

1240
01:13:32,833 --> 01:13:36,543
I did care a lot.

1241
01:13:40,293 --> 01:13:44,723
I came short in expressing that
for you to understand.

1242
01:13:48,073 --> 01:13:49,493
I'm sorry.

1243
01:13:51,683 --> 01:13:53,503
[Daebak incident]

1244
01:13:53,503 --> 01:13:55,003
Really?

1245
01:13:55,793 --> 01:13:57,843
[Glaring]

1246
01:13:59,693 --> 01:14:01,203
No.

1247
01:14:03,153 --> 01:14:04,583
[Wu Yeol carefully expresses his feelings]

1248
01:14:04,583 --> 01:14:06,793
What's going on?

1249
01:14:11,593 --> 01:14:13,743
Of course...

1250
01:14:14,743 --> 01:14:17,553
I wanted to eat sweet potatoes, too.

1251
01:14:17,553 --> 01:14:20,773
When you and Seong Min were making them,

1252
01:14:20,773 --> 01:14:23,643
I wanted to be there, too.

1253
01:14:25,003 --> 01:14:27,443
I wanted to eat that sweet potato.

1254
01:14:28,953 --> 01:14:31,373
[He couldn't approach them]

1255
01:14:31,373 --> 01:14:35,373
[He just circled the perimeters]

1256
01:14:35,373 --> 01:14:36,843
One of them.

1257
01:14:36,843 --> 01:14:38,953
- Sumimasen?
- Daijobu-desu.

1258
01:14:38,953 --> 01:14:43,593
[Wu Yeol was thinking about one thing]

1259
01:14:43,593 --> 01:14:45,233
Daijobu-desu.

1260
01:14:47,083 --> 01:14:48,933
Say it like this.

1261
01:14:48,933 --> 01:14:50,453
What should I do...

1262
01:14:50,453 --> 01:14:52,283
[I'm sorry]

1263
01:14:52,283 --> 01:14:54,133
My goodness...

1264
01:14:59,243 --> 01:15:01,423
I'll be clear from now on.

1265
01:15:01,423 --> 01:15:03,933
Seriously?

1266
01:15:07,133 --> 01:15:10,393
I'm happy that you told me all this.

1267
01:15:11,313 --> 01:15:13,103
Want me to be more detailed?

1268
01:15:13,103 --> 01:15:15,163
- They have so much to say!
- Sure.

1269
01:15:15,163 --> 01:15:16,553
Yes, let it all out.

1270
01:15:16,553 --> 01:15:18,023
That's the happiest moment.

1271
01:15:18,023 --> 01:15:21,153
- Opening up about how you felt.
- Thank you.

1272
01:15:22,183 --> 01:15:24,323
[Grinning]

1273
01:15:24,943 --> 01:15:26,693
So...

1274
01:15:28,293 --> 01:15:30,803
I'm so curious about you.

1275
01:15:30,803 --> 01:15:34,113
- What's your story?
- Ask me anything.

1276
01:15:34,113 --> 01:15:36,033
I'll tell you everything.

1277
01:15:36,033 --> 01:15:39,253
- What's your type?
- Gosh!

1278
01:15:39,253 --> 01:15:43,273
Personality-wise? Or overall?

1279
01:15:44,173 --> 01:15:47,303
I need to be comfortable with someone.

1280
01:15:47,303 --> 01:15:49,983
I'm very comfortable with you.

1281
01:15:49,983 --> 01:15:56,403
Our conversations, our vibes...

1282
01:15:58,533 --> 01:16:00,813
I feel comfortable eating with you tonight.

1283
01:16:00,813 --> 01:16:02,173
Why?

1284
01:16:04,493 --> 01:16:07,543
- Just because.
- Because it's loud in here?

1285
01:16:07,543 --> 01:16:10,053
- The vibe here?
- That, too.

1286
01:16:11,039 --> 01:16:12,855
I have to feel like I can show my true self.

1287
01:16:12,855 --> 01:16:13,458
Yes!

1288
01:16:13,458 --> 01:16:16,433
- I saw this from him tonight.
- Me, too!

1289
01:16:16,433 --> 01:16:20,153
It's the easiest with you.

1290
01:16:25,373 --> 01:16:29,533
I think I can show you more of me, too.

1291
01:16:29,533 --> 01:16:33,253
Okay. Roy Kim for their wedding song.

1292
01:16:33,253 --> 01:16:42,463
When I'm with you,
I want to start conversations.

1293
01:16:43,693 --> 01:16:44,913
[Someone who brings out the real me]

1294
01:16:44,913 --> 01:16:48,873
- I never thought I'd see this from Wu Yeol.
- I know.

1295
01:16:48,873 --> 01:16:53,013
Whether I'm comfortable
with someone or not...

1296
01:16:53,013 --> 01:16:56,353
Honestly, I think I can tell pretty early on.

1297
01:16:56,353 --> 01:16:57,833
When you talk to them?

1298
01:16:57,833 --> 01:17:01,293
When we talked for those 10 minutes...

1299
01:17:01,293 --> 01:17:04,383
I was the most comfortable
with you out of the three.

1300
01:17:04,383 --> 01:17:07,723
- We laughed at each other immediately.
- I know.

1301
01:17:07,723 --> 01:17:11,593
I felt it there.
I'm comfortable with Yu Gyeong.

1302
01:17:15,143 --> 01:17:18,953
- Really?
- She's happy about this.

1303
01:17:20,933 --> 01:17:22,673
That's good.

1304
01:17:30,313 --> 01:17:33,593
- I was so disappointed.
- In Japan?

1305
01:17:33,593 --> 01:17:38,453
In Japan, or around the house...

1306
01:17:38,453 --> 01:17:40,943
Every time we were together,

1307
01:17:43,373 --> 01:17:47,803
I kept noticing you,

1308
01:17:50,063 --> 01:17:53,613
but I couldn't really do anything.

1309
01:17:53,613 --> 01:17:57,933
A few days just passed like that.

1310
01:17:57,933 --> 01:18:01,253
I was so sad that maybe that was it.

1311
01:18:01,253 --> 01:18:02,963
Game over.

1312
01:18:05,493 --> 01:18:08,433
- I had fun on the boat.
- Me, too.

1313
01:18:08,433 --> 01:18:12,093
- We made videos and stuff.
- I know.

1314
01:18:12,093 --> 01:18:13,663
There's a bunch.

1315
01:18:15,523 --> 01:18:17,863
[The first day of the Tokushima trip]

1316
01:18:17,863 --> 01:18:22,593
[Wu Yeol approached Yu Gyeong]

1317
01:18:24,213 --> 01:18:26,103
I'll take the photo.

1318
01:18:27,663 --> 01:18:29,813
Get cozy.

1319
01:18:30,853 --> 01:18:33,983
- Cozy?
- How?

1320
01:18:33,983 --> 01:18:35,333
[Embarrassed]

1321
01:18:35,333 --> 01:18:37,233
How? Just smile?

1322
01:18:41,393 --> 01:18:43,253
[Cracking up]

1323
01:18:44,123 --> 01:18:47,303
I get why you felt that way.
My facial expression.

1324
01:18:47,303 --> 01:18:51,303
- My face sucks.
- No, I was really happy.

1325
01:18:53,123 --> 01:18:54,323
The boat was really nice.

1326
01:18:54,323 --> 01:18:57,193
Right. You came to me.

1327
01:19:00,663 --> 01:19:02,923
Is this allowed?

1328
01:19:02,923 --> 01:19:06,503
There was a small gap
between you and Seo Won.

1329
01:19:06,503 --> 01:19:09,083
- Really?
- He's being honest now.

1330
01:19:09,083 --> 01:19:11,603
I put my hand between you guys.

1331
01:19:11,603 --> 01:19:15,063
I got in there kind of naturally.

1332
01:19:15,063 --> 01:19:17,323
Right. It was pretty cramped.

1333
01:19:17,323 --> 01:19:18,903
Good job.

1334
01:19:20,323 --> 01:19:23,463
That was me putting in effort. Got it?

1335
01:19:23,463 --> 01:19:24,763
That was me putting in effort.

1336
01:19:24,763 --> 01:19:27,013
I see. I felt it then.

1337
01:19:27,013 --> 01:19:28,483
Really?

1338
01:19:29,423 --> 01:19:31,583
I was really happy.

1339
01:19:32,453 --> 01:19:34,493
That was me putting effort in.

1340
01:19:35,723 --> 01:19:37,283
Thank you.

1341
01:19:39,883 --> 01:19:43,813
I love these moments. They can say it now.

1342
01:19:43,813 --> 01:19:46,683
- Are my eyes red?
- Yes.

1343
01:19:47,683 --> 01:19:50,163
Is there anything you want from me?

1344
01:19:53,243 --> 01:19:54,683
[Staring]

1345
01:19:56,463 --> 01:19:59,553
Please say it. Don't say "nothing."

1346
01:20:01,943 --> 01:20:09,583
When someone takes the initiative
to show me how they feel,

1347
01:20:11,173 --> 01:20:13,483
I tend to fall for them.

1348
01:20:14,433 --> 01:20:18,103
But you didn't even do that,

1349
01:20:18,103 --> 01:20:20,823
but I still feel this way.

1350
01:20:23,203 --> 01:20:24,783
Maybe...

1351
01:20:28,433 --> 01:20:31,883
if you were to take initiative...

1352
01:20:34,303 --> 01:20:36,813
I would really like that.

1353
01:20:43,323 --> 01:20:46,253
Got it. Got it.

1354
01:20:46,253 --> 01:20:49,173
How can she be so cute saying that?

1355
01:20:49,173 --> 01:20:50,273
[So pretty]

1356
01:20:50,273 --> 01:20:52,063
My heart is racing.

1357
01:20:52,903 --> 01:20:54,563
[Embarrassed]

1358
01:20:58,793 --> 01:21:01,953
I'm not putting it all on you.

1359
01:21:01,953 --> 01:21:03,683
You can, Yu Gyeong!

1360
01:21:03,683 --> 01:21:06,313
I don't feel that way. I just...

1361
01:21:10,503 --> 01:21:13,793
feel like I wasn't enough.

1362
01:21:16,013 --> 01:21:19,773
Thank you for taking it that way.

1363
01:21:19,773 --> 01:21:23,043
How are they so sweet to one another?

1364
01:21:23,043 --> 01:21:27,403
[Are the two finally connecting?]

1365
01:21:33,333 --> 01:21:35,433
Is there anything you want to do?

1366
01:21:35,433 --> 01:21:37,223
Something I want to do?

1367
01:21:39,543 --> 01:21:41,333
Something I want to do?

1368
01:21:41,333 --> 01:21:43,703
Should we go to a photo booth?

1369
01:21:43,703 --> 01:21:46,263
Photo booth pictures!

1370
01:21:46,263 --> 01:21:49,733
I love it! I never do that.

1371
01:21:49,733 --> 01:21:51,523
Me neither.

1372
01:21:52,993 --> 01:21:56,163
- But I want to do it with you.
- Let's do it.

1373
01:21:57,273 --> 01:22:00,623
[Whatever it is, I'll do it if it's with you]

1374
01:22:01,373 --> 01:22:04,443
What? Let's take some nice pictures.

1375
01:22:04,443 --> 01:22:06,343
I don't know.

1376
01:22:09,253 --> 01:22:11,483
Can we do the flower pose?

1377
01:22:11,483 --> 01:22:12,843
The flower pose...

1378
01:22:12,843 --> 01:22:15,983
- You don't want to do that?
- Not that.

1379
01:22:16,773 --> 01:22:18,333
How about this?

1380
01:22:28,613 --> 01:22:31,273
[On their way to the photo booth,
all excited]

1381
01:22:31,273 --> 01:22:34,883
- I'm excited. This sounds fun.
- Where is it?

1382
01:22:35,813 --> 01:22:37,953
I'm going on the left.

1383
01:22:39,883 --> 01:22:42,813
Want four of these or four of these?

1384
01:22:42,813 --> 01:22:44,943
I think the smaller one will be cuter.

1385
01:22:44,943 --> 01:22:46,793
The smaller one?

1386
01:22:48,203 --> 01:22:50,793
- Want to do the lines?
- Yes.

1387
01:22:50,793 --> 01:22:53,893
[Click, side by side]

1388
01:22:55,063 --> 01:22:56,813
- Is it okay?
- Yes.

1389
01:22:58,543 --> 01:23:03,703
[One more shot making peace signs]

1390
01:23:03,703 --> 01:23:07,053
- Oppa, get in front of me.
- Okay.

1391
01:23:07,053 --> 01:23:08,643
I'll do this.

1392
01:23:08,643 --> 01:23:10,663
[A little closer this time]

1393
01:23:14,613 --> 01:23:15,883
How about for the last one?

1394
01:23:15,883 --> 01:23:17,153
What do you want to do?

1395
01:23:17,153 --> 01:23:18,933
Should I get close?

1396
01:23:22,203 --> 01:23:23,273
[Sliding]

1397
01:23:23,973 --> 01:23:25,513
Pick.

1398
01:23:26,463 --> 01:23:28,633
This one is better, right?

1399
01:23:28,633 --> 01:23:31,923
- I like this one up close.
- This one is cute, too.

1400
01:23:32,833 --> 01:23:34,683
They look good.

1401
01:23:38,303 --> 01:23:41,153
They're good. Next time...

1402
01:23:41,153 --> 01:23:43,273
Let's come back when we're clearheaded.

1403
01:23:43,273 --> 01:23:45,113
We'll come back in the morning.

1404
01:23:45,113 --> 01:23:46,913
In the morning?

1405
01:23:46,913 --> 01:23:49,353
- Do you want one?
- Oh, my goodness.

1406
01:23:49,353 --> 01:23:50,713
Mixed up?

1407
01:23:50,713 --> 01:23:53,773
Walnut and peanut mixed? Sounds good.

1408
01:23:55,503 --> 01:23:58,523
This looks so good. I've been craving it.

1409
01:23:58,523 --> 01:24:00,653
Thank you!

1410
01:24:01,673 --> 01:24:04,103
- Try it first.
- You want me to test it?

1411
01:24:04,103 --> 01:24:07,713
- He's feeding her again.
- It's burnt.

1412
01:24:07,713 --> 01:24:09,123
There's a car.

1413
01:24:09,123 --> 01:24:11,283
I thought they were going to link arms.

1414
01:24:13,023 --> 01:24:16,003
- Let's try the walnut one.
- You want the walnut?

1415
01:24:20,403 --> 01:24:22,893
He keeps feeding her!

1416
01:24:26,403 --> 01:24:28,343
[In the car post-date]

1417
01:24:28,343 --> 01:24:31,183
Did you like the walnut better
or the peanut one?

1418
01:24:31,183 --> 01:24:32,683
I like walnut cookies.

1419
01:24:32,683 --> 01:24:34,493
- Really?
- Yes.

1420
01:24:35,463 --> 01:24:38,293
[Glancing]

1421
01:24:43,643 --> 01:24:46,453
You seem a little sweeter.

1422
01:24:46,453 --> 01:24:49,463
- Yes, we feel it, too.
- Really?

1423
01:24:49,463 --> 01:24:51,943
What makes you say that?

1424
01:24:52,803 --> 01:24:55,173
I don't know. It just feels like it.

1425
01:24:58,983 --> 01:25:00,233
[Reaching]

1426
01:25:00,233 --> 01:25:02,313
So sweet.

1427
01:25:04,833 --> 01:25:07,503
So sweet.

1428
01:25:07,503 --> 01:25:10,603
- The best.
- She said "The best."

1429
01:25:16,303 --> 01:25:18,633
I don't want to go home.

1430
01:25:18,633 --> 01:25:20,023
Right?

1431
01:25:20,993 --> 01:25:22,513
Me neither.

1432
01:25:23,553 --> 01:25:25,313
I'm sad.

1433
01:25:28,603 --> 01:25:30,753
[They keep making eye contact]

1434
01:25:31,353 --> 01:25:34,173
Is this when we go to the tea room?

1435
01:25:35,713 --> 01:25:40,553
Our first tea room?

1436
01:25:40,553 --> 01:25:42,443
Sounds great.

1437
01:25:44,153 --> 01:25:45,503
My heart is racing.

1438
01:25:45,503 --> 01:25:47,663
What do we do now?

1439
01:25:47,663 --> 01:25:49,333
What do we try to guess?

1440
01:25:49,333 --> 01:25:51,223
There are six people!

1441
01:25:51,223 --> 01:25:54,153
I'm scared now that things
are working out for them.

1442
01:25:54,153 --> 01:25:55,683
Because it might fall apart.

1443
01:25:55,683 --> 01:25:56,883
- I know.
- Right.

1444
01:25:56,883 --> 01:25:59,193
He's basically set on Yu Gyeong, right?

1445
01:25:59,193 --> 01:26:00,243
Yes.

1446
01:26:00,243 --> 01:26:03,993
The most "sixth-sense" thing I felt was...

1447
01:26:03,993 --> 01:26:06,603
When he asked her, "Do you know
what I did to approach you?"

1448
01:26:06,603 --> 01:26:08,523
Yu Gyeong knew.

1449
01:26:08,523 --> 01:26:12,353
From our perspective, that was such a twist.

1450
01:26:12,353 --> 01:26:14,443
For Yu Gyeong, tonight is great.

1451
01:26:14,443 --> 01:26:17,883
A man who made her sweat by being wishy-washy

1452
01:26:17,883 --> 01:26:20,003
finally told her, "It's you."

1453
01:26:20,003 --> 01:26:24,403
She asked if she could trust him,
and he said yes.

1454
01:26:24,403 --> 01:26:26,183
Yeah! It's over!

1455
01:26:26,183 --> 01:26:29,183
More than anything,
it was his saying "sorry."

1456
01:26:29,183 --> 01:26:31,593
- That made my heart skip.
- It was the best.

1457
01:26:31,593 --> 01:26:32,793
I melted.

1458
01:26:32,793 --> 01:26:36,703
He's admitting that he's been wishy-washy.

1459
01:26:36,703 --> 01:26:40,303
- Right.
- Wu Yeol tried to show

1460
01:26:40,303 --> 01:26:43,193
that he liked her, in his own way.

1461
01:26:43,193 --> 01:26:45,173
- But she didn't feel it.
- It was too subtle.

1462
01:26:45,173 --> 01:26:48,353
"I'm sorry that it didn't come across."

1463
01:26:48,353 --> 01:26:52,863
There were two lovely moments for Yu Gyeong.

1464
01:26:52,863 --> 01:26:56,043
That moment when she wrung herself inward.

1465
01:26:56,043 --> 01:27:03,453
Second, when she said, "If you took
initiative, I'd like that."

1466
01:27:03,453 --> 01:27:05,233
- She was beautiful.
- Right.

1467
01:27:05,233 --> 01:27:08,513
If you can just show me,
I'd like you even more.

1468
01:27:08,513 --> 01:27:11,803
Wu Yeol laid it down. Is it a done deal?

1469
01:27:11,803 --> 01:27:14,563
- I pick Yu Gyeong!
- Of course, it's a done deal.

1470
01:27:14,563 --> 01:27:16,393
As of now.

1471
01:27:16,393 --> 01:27:18,903
Right now, it's totally a done deal.

1472
01:27:18,903 --> 01:27:21,533
But in a few days, this might happen.

1473
01:27:21,533 --> 01:27:23,723
That was just a placeholder stamp...

1474
01:27:23,723 --> 01:27:26,233
Here's the real one!

1475
01:27:27,683 --> 01:27:31,413
[Huam-dong, Yongsan-gu]

1476
01:27:31,413 --> 01:27:35,613
[Seo Won and Gyu Ri arrive
at their next location]

1477
01:27:35,613 --> 01:27:37,383
Hello!

1478
01:27:37,383 --> 01:27:39,253
Hello.

1479
01:27:39,253 --> 01:27:41,523
This is a full date.

1480
01:27:41,523 --> 01:27:44,143
This is nice.

1481
01:27:44,143 --> 01:27:45,383
What do you want to get?

1482
01:27:45,383 --> 01:27:47,673
Wine. Red.

1483
01:27:47,673 --> 01:27:50,493
- Let's have red wine together.
- Sounds good.

1484
01:27:50,493 --> 01:27:52,623
I just want wine.

1485
01:27:52,623 --> 01:27:54,173
Sounds good.

1486
01:27:57,253 --> 01:27:59,563
I like how private this is.

1487
01:27:59,563 --> 01:28:01,443
I feel at ease.

1488
01:28:01,443 --> 01:28:05,433
I felt a little bit under pressure...

1489
01:28:05,433 --> 01:28:08,333
- A little intimidated.
- I think so.

1490
01:28:08,333 --> 01:28:10,233
I'm so at ease right now.

1491
01:28:10,233 --> 01:28:11,813
[Fidgeting]

1492
01:28:12,593 --> 01:28:17,023
[The comfort of darkness and quiet]

1493
01:28:18,103 --> 01:28:20,443
I like seats like these.

1494
01:28:20,443 --> 01:28:22,413
So you can see someone's profile?

1495
01:28:22,413 --> 01:28:24,443
[Ahh]

1496
01:28:24,443 --> 01:28:25,723
I think so.

1497
01:28:25,723 --> 01:28:28,053
Maybe that's why.

1498
01:28:28,053 --> 01:28:31,503
It's hard for me to make eye contact head-on.

1499
01:28:31,503 --> 01:28:37,003
- I like face to face.
- My eyes just go like this.

1500
01:28:39,453 --> 01:28:43,253
- It requires courage to be face-to-face.
- Yes.

1501
01:28:47,033 --> 01:28:52,223
We got a little closer today,
thanks to crying together.

1502
01:28:53,593 --> 01:28:56,563
We cried so much.

1503
01:28:56,563 --> 01:28:58,843
My face stings.

1504
01:28:58,843 --> 01:29:02,953
I don't think it'd be sad.
Isn't it just romance?

1505
01:29:05,773 --> 01:29:07,493
So cute!

1506
01:29:07,493 --> 01:29:09,333
[Sobbing while watching romance]

1507
01:29:11,573 --> 01:29:12,633
[Glancing]

1508
01:29:12,633 --> 01:29:13,803
Oh, no...

1509
01:29:13,803 --> 01:29:15,203
[Cracking up]

1510
01:29:18,293 --> 01:29:21,773
He cried for an hour next to me.

1511
01:29:21,773 --> 01:29:22,863
So cute.

1512
01:29:22,863 --> 01:29:25,443
I cried like there was no tomorrow.

1513
01:29:26,343 --> 01:29:32,253
We cried at the same scene, I think.

1514
01:29:32,253 --> 01:29:34,493
"It's going to work out for you,
no matter what."

1515
01:29:34,493 --> 01:29:36,473
- That made me cry.
- People talk about that line a lot.

1516
01:29:36,473 --> 01:29:41,703
Between someone who supports
and encourages you endlessly,

1517
01:29:41,703 --> 01:29:48,183
and someone
who gives you solutions with facts.

1518
01:29:48,183 --> 01:29:54,723
Even just two years ago,
I liked the solutions person.

1519
01:29:54,723 --> 01:29:57,443
But that changed.

1520
01:29:57,443 --> 01:30:00,453
Encouragement is the real deal.

1521
01:30:00,453 --> 01:30:03,113
- The person has a situation.
- Right. You can't fully understand.

1522
01:30:03,113 --> 01:30:06,173
It's impossible to fully understand...

1523
01:30:06,173 --> 01:30:11,713
I always write down, "At your own pace."

1524
01:30:11,713 --> 01:30:16,013
You don't have to worry about being
faster or slower than others.

1525
01:30:19,653 --> 01:30:21,803
I needed to hear that.

1526
01:30:23,063 --> 01:30:28,383
But despite the fact that I've been
running with no breaks,

1527
01:30:28,383 --> 01:30:33,213
I don't know how to comfort
myself, or anything like that.

1528
01:30:33,213 --> 01:30:35,493
I'm not good at it.

1529
01:30:35,493 --> 01:30:38,353
I need someone who can do that.

1530
01:30:39,553 --> 01:30:41,373
[Looking]

1531
01:30:41,373 --> 01:30:45,683
When people ask me
how I want to live my life,

1532
01:30:45,683 --> 01:30:50,393
I say, "I want to be happy.
Optimistic. Positive."

1533
01:30:50,393 --> 01:30:55,223
I try to see the wine glass as half full.

1534
01:30:56,633 --> 01:30:58,733
I think it's important.

1535
01:31:01,433 --> 01:31:04,383
I felt that, too.

1536
01:31:09,143 --> 01:31:13,793
Someone who is always so optimistic...

1537
01:31:16,123 --> 01:31:17,413
You...

1538
01:31:18,283 --> 01:31:23,133
Looking at you, Seo Won...

1539
01:31:23,133 --> 01:31:27,643
I feel good energy.

1540
01:31:27,643 --> 01:31:31,183
That's how I felt.

1541
01:31:35,083 --> 01:31:38,363
- I just keep feeling bad.
- About what?

1542
01:31:38,363 --> 01:31:40,843
I feel like we should be having more fun.

1543
01:31:40,843 --> 01:31:42,863
I am having a lot of fun right now.

1544
01:31:42,863 --> 01:31:46,723
I feel way too calm right now.

1545
01:31:46,723 --> 01:31:48,073
Gyu Ri feels bad, too.

1546
01:31:48,073 --> 01:31:49,993
That's part of your charm.

1547
01:31:51,133 --> 01:31:55,923
It's natural that a date between
us two feels different

1548
01:31:55,923 --> 01:31:58,333
from when we're in a big group.

1549
01:32:00,623 --> 01:32:01,573
I think it's okay.

1550
01:32:01,573 --> 01:32:04,533
- He's a nice guy. Very sensitive.
- Very much so.

1551
01:32:04,533 --> 01:32:09,443
[Calm attractiveness meets bright energy]

1552
01:32:09,443 --> 01:32:16,523
I think I get a good sense
after a few conversations.

1553
01:32:16,523 --> 01:32:19,513
I can tell someone's personality.

1554
01:32:20,493 --> 01:32:24,903
But I had the hardest time with you.

1555
01:32:24,903 --> 01:32:28,273
Me? Why is that?

1556
01:32:28,273 --> 01:32:32,923
On the first night, we took turns
and talked, remember?

1557
01:32:32,923 --> 01:32:34,693
Right, that was a problem.

1558
01:32:34,693 --> 01:32:37,163
He should have given her a better impression!

1559
01:32:37,163 --> 01:32:38,853
[Seo Won looked cold in their first 1:1]

1560
01:32:38,853 --> 01:32:41,163
- Goodbye.
- Right, he was like that.

1561
01:32:41,163 --> 01:32:42,393
Take care.

1562
01:32:42,393 --> 01:32:46,133
The candle incident.

1563
01:32:46,133 --> 01:32:48,503
As soon as the flame went off,
you looked at me...

1564
01:32:48,503 --> 01:32:50,603
You said, "Goodbye."

1565
01:32:50,603 --> 01:32:53,253
[Embarrassed]

1566
01:32:53,253 --> 01:32:56,083
I'm going to remember that forever.

1567
01:32:56,083 --> 01:32:57,133
Why?

1568
01:32:57,133 --> 01:33:00,453
"What was the saddest moment of your life?'

1569
01:33:00,453 --> 01:33:04,093
There was this guy named Seo Won...

1570
01:33:04,093 --> 01:33:06,843
- No way.
- He was unique in the first episode.

1571
01:33:06,843 --> 01:33:08,473
We were wondering if he went too far.

1572
01:33:08,473 --> 01:33:11,683
Anyway, I couldn't figure you out.

1573
01:33:11,683 --> 01:33:14,713
But once I did...

1574
01:33:16,103 --> 01:33:20,363
you're the best.

1575
01:33:20,363 --> 01:33:22,003
We feel the same.

1576
01:33:22,003 --> 01:33:25,013
[In retrospect, it was the best memory]

1577
01:33:25,993 --> 01:33:31,143
When we were talking about the first book...

1578
01:33:31,143 --> 01:33:34,993
I saw a thoughtful side of you.

1579
01:33:34,993 --> 01:33:38,453
I felt like that was different.

1580
01:33:41,763 --> 01:33:43,903
I think you have to get to know someone.

1581
01:33:43,903 --> 01:33:45,413
Seo Won has a lot on his mind.

1582
01:33:45,413 --> 01:33:47,163
[Fidgeting]

1583
01:33:48,333 --> 01:33:52,313
[Staring]

1584
01:33:52,313 --> 01:33:56,973
Now that we've gotten to know each other 1:1,

1585
01:33:56,973 --> 01:34:00,423
I feel like we have some things in common.

1586
01:34:00,423 --> 01:34:04,733
It's a little bit unexpected, in a good way.

1587
01:34:05,693 --> 01:34:08,553
I want to bring out more of that.

1588
01:34:08,553 --> 01:34:12,263
That's why I feel like
I'm lacking in some way.

1589
01:34:12,263 --> 01:34:14,273
I'm crazy.

1590
01:34:17,083 --> 01:34:18,973
You are?

1591
01:34:19,813 --> 01:34:24,033
Sometimes, I lower the car window and scream.

1592
01:34:24,033 --> 01:34:26,183
Really?

1593
01:34:26,183 --> 01:34:29,443
After the first shy phase of dating is over,

1594
01:34:29,443 --> 01:34:33,183
I sing BigBang songs, and I scream.
I go crazy.

1595
01:34:34,123 --> 01:34:41,013
[Are their hearts a little bit more open?]

1596
01:34:45,063 --> 01:34:50,753
But you know, in Japan...

1597
01:34:51,743 --> 01:34:53,823
I was really nervous.

1598
01:34:53,823 --> 01:34:59,423
Because I had to win
and get the one I wanted.

1599
01:35:00,363 --> 01:35:03,023
But today...

1600
01:35:03,023 --> 01:35:05,923
I'm speaking casually to feel more at ease.

1601
01:35:05,923 --> 01:35:07,763
Right.

1602
01:35:07,763 --> 01:35:09,423
So...

1603
01:35:10,723 --> 01:35:12,673
I looked forward to it.

1604
01:35:14,453 --> 01:35:15,613
[Staring]

1605
01:35:15,613 --> 01:35:17,903
Right!

1606
01:35:18,903 --> 01:35:19,933
Actually...

1607
01:35:19,933 --> 01:35:22,253
- That's right!
- What is it?

1608
01:35:23,573 --> 01:35:26,333
I was thinking about this at night.

1609
01:35:26,333 --> 01:35:29,223
I wanted to go on a date with you, Noona.

1610
01:35:29,223 --> 01:35:33,393
I thought about it before I went
to bed the first night.

1611
01:35:33,393 --> 01:35:35,143
I wanted to go on a date with you.

1612
01:35:35,143 --> 01:35:37,493
Hearing that while saying "Noona"
makes my heart skip a beat.

1613
01:35:37,493 --> 01:35:40,993
I waited, but I didn't know it was you.

1614
01:35:41,893 --> 01:35:43,633
That was cool.

1615
01:35:44,833 --> 01:35:46,783
We were on the same page.

1616
01:35:48,343 --> 01:35:53,093
Our time in Japan was valuable. But...

1617
01:35:53,993 --> 01:35:56,133
the weekends are also valuable.

1618
01:35:59,413 --> 01:36:02,303
I wanted to spend the weekend with you again.

1619
01:36:02,303 --> 01:36:05,523
- So honest.
- He's confessing.

1620
01:36:05,523 --> 01:36:06,853
I see.

1621
01:36:06,853 --> 01:36:09,583
Yes, just look at him.

1622
01:36:14,753 --> 01:36:17,973
So, what do you think? No regrets?

1623
01:36:18,953 --> 01:36:21,373
I never regret my decisions.

1624
01:36:25,393 --> 01:36:28,873
Now that we've seen a movie,

1625
01:36:28,873 --> 01:36:31,003
there's something else I want to do.

1626
01:36:31,003 --> 01:36:35,303
- What is it?
- Clock out of Signal House

1627
01:36:35,303 --> 01:36:41,603
and eat a late-night meal together.
I want to try that.

1628
01:36:41,603 --> 01:36:43,633
With me? Or...

1629
01:36:44,823 --> 01:36:47,403
Yes. That would be nice.

1630
01:36:48,403 --> 01:36:52,703
[Can't hide his smile]

1631
01:36:55,233 --> 01:36:58,133
[Seo Won leaves for a moment]

1632
01:36:58,133 --> 01:37:00,553
I just paid. We can go.

1633
01:37:00,553 --> 01:37:01,953
- Who?
- How thoughtful!

1634
01:37:01,953 --> 01:37:04,713
- He's doing great.
- You paid?

1635
01:37:05,593 --> 01:37:08,243
- Why did you?
- It's okay.

1636
01:37:08,243 --> 01:37:10,133
It's okay. Hush.

1637
01:37:12,883 --> 01:37:15,603
Treat me to something tasty next time.

1638
01:37:15,603 --> 01:37:16,743
Got it.

1639
01:37:16,743 --> 01:37:18,073
Everything was perfect.

1640
01:37:18,073 --> 01:37:22,733
If I book omakase, will you go?

1641
01:37:22,733 --> 01:37:26,523
- I really want to feed you sometime.
- "Feed you."

1642
01:37:26,523 --> 01:37:29,783
- You've been to omakase a lot, huh?
- Me?

1643
01:37:30,693 --> 01:37:33,383
- I'm not that kind of kid.
- Really?

1644
01:37:33,383 --> 01:37:34,593
You haven't?

1645
01:37:34,593 --> 01:37:36,203
What is sushi?

1646
01:37:36,203 --> 01:37:38,433
[Cracking up]

1647
01:37:38,433 --> 01:37:40,663
What is sushi anyway?

1648
01:37:42,403 --> 01:37:43,793
That was a good ending.

1649
01:37:43,793 --> 01:37:46,053
So nice.

1650
01:37:47,053 --> 01:37:48,563
[Lingering emotions]

1651
01:37:48,563 --> 01:37:50,323
- Seo Won, you did it.
- I know.

1652
01:37:50,323 --> 01:37:54,513
Seo Won went for it more
cautiously than I expected.

1653
01:37:54,513 --> 01:37:57,543
"I'm so happy I'm on a date with you, Noona."

1654
01:37:57,543 --> 01:38:00,973
We couldn't even do that at our age.

1655
01:38:00,973 --> 01:38:03,723
What I liked was that I could feel

1656
01:38:03,723 --> 01:38:07,513
Gyu Ri wanted to have a good time
with Seo Won.

1657
01:38:07,513 --> 01:38:10,473
That made me rethink Gyu Ri.

1658
01:38:10,473 --> 01:38:13,853
Maybe running into Wu Yeol and
Yu Gyeong at the movies

1659
01:38:13,853 --> 01:38:17,493
reduced her interest in Wu Yeol

1660
01:38:17,493 --> 01:38:19,653
which opened the door for Seo Won.

1661
01:38:19,653 --> 01:38:22,683
I don't think she could come back
from falling for Seo Won,

1662
01:38:22,683 --> 01:38:24,593
who can handle anything.

1663
01:38:24,593 --> 01:38:28,033
Of course, that might go away
once Wu Yeol is back.

1664
01:38:28,033 --> 01:38:30,923
Wu Yeol is like Deus Ex Machina.

1665
01:38:30,923 --> 01:38:33,713
When he appears, everything resets.

1666
01:38:33,713 --> 01:38:37,653
This couple depends on what Wu Yeol does.

1667
01:38:37,653 --> 01:38:41,963
I think Seo Won is careful
because he knows that.

1668
01:38:41,963 --> 01:38:43,393
- I agree.
- Right?

1669
01:38:43,393 --> 01:38:45,523
Seo Won is conscious of it.

1670
01:38:45,523 --> 01:38:47,223
He can see it.

1671
01:38:47,223 --> 01:38:49,003
Let's go in.

1672
01:38:49,003 --> 01:38:51,753
[Seo Won and Gyu Ri arrive at the house]

1673
01:38:52,363 --> 01:38:56,853
- No one is on the first floor.
- That couple isn't here.

1674
01:38:58,573 --> 01:39:03,153
[The house is empty]

1675
01:39:05,463 --> 01:39:09,173
Is this real? No one is home?

1676
01:39:13,473 --> 01:39:17,413
[They change into comfortable clothes]

1677
01:39:19,033 --> 01:39:20,463
[Yu Gyeong and Wu Yeol get home second]

1678
01:39:20,463 --> 01:39:22,833
Yu Gyeong and Wu Yeol are back, too.

1679
01:39:22,833 --> 01:39:24,153
Is anyone here?

1680
01:39:24,153 --> 01:39:26,003
Can you wear the smaller ones?

1681
01:39:26,003 --> 01:39:30,243
Wait. That one is bigger.

1682
01:39:31,323 --> 01:39:33,883
It's mismatched.

1683
01:39:35,913 --> 01:39:37,323
Here.

1684
01:39:37,323 --> 01:39:40,703
[Keeping the movie ticket]

1685
01:39:41,583 --> 01:39:44,473
Let's change clothes and meet after.

1686
01:39:44,473 --> 01:39:46,163
Yo! You're back.

1687
01:39:46,163 --> 01:39:49,953
- Alone?
- No, I'm with Gyu Ri.

1688
01:39:49,953 --> 01:39:52,673
Did you have fun? How was your date?

1689
01:39:52,673 --> 01:39:54,413
Was it good?

1690
01:39:54,413 --> 01:39:57,643
- Where did you go after the movie?
- We ate pork belly and pork skirt.

1691
01:39:57,643 --> 01:39:59,833
You said you wanted that.

1692
01:39:59,833 --> 01:40:01,403
- So you had that.
- We had that and soju.

1693
01:40:01,403 --> 01:40:03,883
- Soju?
- Somaek. Soju.

1694
01:40:04,783 --> 01:40:08,403
We went to a bar. An LP bar nearby.

1695
01:40:08,403 --> 01:40:12,963
We ate, watched a movie, and then
went to an LP bar. Three.

1696
01:40:13,963 --> 01:40:16,263
You totally used a cheat code today.

1697
01:40:16,263 --> 01:40:18,243
- Cheat code?
- A conversation between friends.

1698
01:40:18,243 --> 01:40:20,893
What do you mean a cheat code?

1699
01:40:22,743 --> 01:40:25,003
They're not talking about the movie.

1700
01:40:25,003 --> 01:40:26,723
[Toss]

1701
01:40:34,443 --> 01:40:37,573
- Unni!
- I had no idea.

1702
01:40:37,573 --> 01:40:39,673
I just got back.

1703
01:40:39,673 --> 01:40:42,543
No one's here.

1704
01:40:42,543 --> 01:40:44,533
- The others?
- Yeah.

1705
01:40:45,883 --> 01:40:48,243
Were you crying at the movie?

1706
01:40:48,243 --> 01:40:52,203
- No.
- Really? Neither of you cried?

1707
01:40:52,203 --> 01:40:56,363
Wow, we were the total opposite.
Seo Won and I...

1708
01:40:56,363 --> 01:40:58,733
- You cried? Really?
- Sobbing.

1709
01:40:58,733 --> 01:41:01,873
We just kept crying.

1710
01:41:04,203 --> 01:41:05,373
Wow.

1711
01:41:05,373 --> 01:41:08,303
- Neither of you cried? Not Wu Yeol?
- No.

1712
01:41:08,303 --> 01:41:11,203
- She was wondering about Wu Yeol.
- Daebak.

1713
01:41:12,363 --> 01:41:14,593
We are so different.

1714
01:41:15,723 --> 01:41:17,593
[Focused]

1715
01:41:18,963 --> 01:41:21,473
Are you journaling?

1716
01:41:22,893 --> 01:41:25,243
The day went by so fast.

1717
01:41:25,243 --> 01:41:27,163
I'm curious.

1718
01:41:27,163 --> 01:41:29,543
- How did you end up at Gangnam?
- They're talking about it!

1719
01:41:29,543 --> 01:41:31,693
How did you end up at the Gangnam theater?

1720
01:41:31,693 --> 01:41:33,693
I picked it, and somehow...

1721
01:41:33,693 --> 01:41:35,533
- I had no idea.
- Really?

1722
01:41:35,533 --> 01:41:38,143
That was the only place
at that time with middle seats.

1723
01:41:38,143 --> 01:41:40,743
There were exactly two seats open.

1724
01:41:40,743 --> 01:41:43,403
I handpicked that location, seats, and time.

1725
01:41:43,403 --> 01:41:47,563
- The time, too?
- Yes! I had no clue!

1726
01:41:47,563 --> 01:41:49,423
I picked it. I bought the tickets.

1727
01:41:49,423 --> 01:41:50,683
Same.

1728
01:41:50,683 --> 01:41:52,413
That time at Gangnam?

1729
01:41:52,413 --> 01:41:53,443
Coincidentally?

1730
01:41:53,443 --> 01:41:55,573
Stop lying!

1731
01:41:55,573 --> 01:41:58,883
I was talking to Yu Gyeong here yesterday.

1732
01:41:58,883 --> 01:42:00,683
We were here.

1733
01:42:00,683 --> 01:42:02,273
We had already bought the tickets.

1734
01:42:02,273 --> 01:42:04,743
Really? Then I did it after.

1735
01:42:04,743 --> 01:42:06,873
I did it after.

1736
01:42:06,873 --> 01:42:09,683
[A coincidence more cinematic
than the cinema]

1737
01:42:09,683 --> 01:42:11,573
For real?

1738
01:42:12,463 --> 01:42:13,583
[Click]

1739
01:42:16,113 --> 01:42:20,883
[Gyu Ri is taking a break]

1740
01:42:25,203 --> 01:42:26,623
Daebak. No way.

1741
01:42:26,623 --> 01:42:30,563
I heard you were sobbing.

1742
01:42:30,563 --> 01:42:32,173
Didn't you cry?

1743
01:42:32,173 --> 01:42:33,623
We didn't cry.

1744
01:42:33,623 --> 01:42:37,913
Gosh, I can't talk to Ts.

1745
01:42:38,813 --> 01:42:41,643
- I did tear up a little.
- It was crazy.

1746
01:42:41,643 --> 01:42:43,893
I've never cried so much before.

1747
01:42:43,893 --> 01:42:45,253
Did you sob continuously?

1748
01:42:45,253 --> 01:42:46,393
An hour?

1749
01:42:46,393 --> 01:42:48,423
[A conversation between polar opposites]

1750
01:42:48,423 --> 01:42:51,653
I thought I'd feel awkward seeing
the person when I got back.

1751
01:42:51,653 --> 01:42:55,063
But it was nice to see again.
Don't you think?

1752
01:42:55,063 --> 01:42:57,113
Let's go. Thank you.

1753
01:42:57,113 --> 01:43:00,563
The happiest moment for me today
was hearing your footsteps.

1754
01:43:01,493 --> 01:43:03,153
Huh? No one is here.

1755
01:43:03,153 --> 01:43:04,873
Gosh, seriously...

1756
01:43:04,873 --> 01:43:06,703
- They're here.
- They are?

1757
01:43:06,703 --> 01:43:08,893
We were both sobbing.

1758
01:43:08,893 --> 01:43:10,673
- Hey.
- What's going on?

1759
01:43:10,673 --> 01:43:14,433
- Hello.
- Is Gyu Ri here?

1760
01:43:14,433 --> 01:43:17,933
I was at work
and heard that they were eating.

1761
01:43:17,933 --> 01:43:20,283
[The tenants are all in the house]

1762
01:43:20,283 --> 01:43:22,333
Did you enjoy the movie?

1763
01:43:22,333 --> 01:43:23,803
Was the movie good?

1764
01:43:23,803 --> 01:43:27,703
- How far did the rumor spread?
- I cried.

1765
01:43:27,703 --> 01:43:28,993
Four and four.

1766
01:43:28,993 --> 01:43:32,043
- What did you do? Did you meet after work?
- Yeah, after work.

1767
01:43:32,043 --> 01:43:34,533
- Did the four of you hang out?
- No.

1768
01:43:34,533 --> 01:43:36,903
- Two and two?
- We ran into each other.

1769
01:43:36,903 --> 01:43:39,503
- We bumped into each other.
- By accident. Really.

1770
01:43:39,503 --> 01:43:42,823
- Don't lie.
- I have proof.

1771
01:43:42,823 --> 01:43:45,223
There's no way. A twist of fate.

1772
01:43:45,223 --> 01:43:47,763
Gyu Ri is sleeping.

1773
01:43:47,763 --> 01:43:51,053
She said she'd rest until the Self Talk.

1774
01:43:51,053 --> 01:43:53,243
She must be tired.

1775
01:43:53,243 --> 01:43:56,733
Did you all have fun?
We probably had the most fun.

1776
01:43:56,733 --> 01:43:59,973
[Starts out strong]

1777
01:43:59,973 --> 01:44:03,543
But honestly, this isn't bluffing.

1778
01:44:03,543 --> 01:44:05,623
I was so shocked when I arrived.

1779
01:44:05,623 --> 01:44:09,123
Have you seen "Parasite"?

1780
01:44:09,123 --> 01:44:12,123
- Respect. Really.
- We did everything.

1781
01:44:12,123 --> 01:44:13,413
Respect. Seriously.

1782
01:44:13,413 --> 01:44:15,253
- You want ice cream?
- Why didn't you come?

1783
01:44:15,253 --> 01:44:17,953
So, why did you go off on dates two by two?

1784
01:44:17,953 --> 01:44:20,733
You missed out on a fun talk.

1785
01:44:20,733 --> 01:44:22,323
Sorry.

1786
01:44:23,153 --> 01:44:26,423
- Daebak.
- They're being affected!

1787
01:44:26,423 --> 01:44:28,893
- Melona?
- Whoa!

1788
01:44:28,893 --> 01:44:30,903
[Playing around]

1789
01:44:30,903 --> 01:44:32,693
[The two seem closer after the date]

1790
01:44:32,693 --> 01:44:35,463
They totally grew close.

1791
01:44:36,823 --> 01:44:40,563
[The bell rings in the house]

1792
01:44:44,113 --> 01:44:45,853
Oh, my God.

1793
01:44:45,853 --> 01:44:49,053
[Headache]

1794
01:44:49,053 --> 01:44:53,923
[Did you detect their heart signals?]

1795
01:44:53,923 --> 01:44:57,873
[Predict the eight people's
love lines based on clues!]

1796
01:44:57,873 --> 01:44:59,663
Who's the easiest person today?

1797
01:44:59,663 --> 01:45:01,433
- Park Wu Yeol.
- Right.

1798
01:45:01,433 --> 01:45:03,773
Did we ever start with Wu Yeol before?

1799
01:45:03,773 --> 01:45:05,943
He was good today. Good.

1800
01:45:05,943 --> 01:45:09,293
- He didn't make us think today.
- So easy.

1801
01:45:09,293 --> 01:45:11,713
- Yu Gyeong, too.
- Totally easy.

1802
01:45:11,713 --> 01:45:14,713
- This is it.
- Good.

1803
01:45:14,713 --> 01:45:16,883
Seo Won is easy, too.

1804
01:45:16,883 --> 01:45:19,033
The couples who went on dates are easy.

1805
01:45:19,033 --> 01:45:21,613
Seo Won is easy, too.

1806
01:45:21,613 --> 01:45:23,663
Gyu Ri will probably pick Seo Won, right?

1807
01:45:23,663 --> 01:45:25,853
They were never this easy.

1808
01:45:25,853 --> 01:45:28,023
Min Ju? Let's start with Min Ju.

1809
01:45:28,023 --> 01:45:30,263
Min Ju will choose Seong Min.

1810
01:45:30,263 --> 01:45:32,593
Seong Min will choose Min Ju, too.

1811
01:45:32,593 --> 01:45:35,043
Easy. Seong Min will, of course...

1812
01:45:35,043 --> 01:45:36,523
- Seong Min for Min Ju, too?
- Yes, Min Ju.

1813
01:45:36,523 --> 01:45:38,023
Seemed like Seong Min would choose Min Ju.

1814
01:45:38,023 --> 01:45:39,453
I say Seong Min for Min Ju.

1815
01:45:39,453 --> 01:45:41,343
Let's go with that.

1816
01:45:41,343 --> 01:45:42,853
[So Yun's choice is?]

1817
01:45:42,853 --> 01:45:44,293
Wu Yeol.

1818
01:45:44,293 --> 01:45:45,843
You think she'd say "I missed you"?

1819
01:45:45,843 --> 01:45:48,353
What do you think she'd say in her text?

1820
01:45:48,353 --> 01:45:49,653
"Take the ring."

1821
01:45:49,653 --> 01:45:54,243
No. I'd say we go with what we saw onscreen.

1822
01:45:54,243 --> 01:45:56,023
Then, So Yun is too tough.

1823
01:45:56,023 --> 01:45:58,903
We're guessing she didn't text Wu Yeol.

1824
01:45:58,903 --> 01:46:01,643
But based on what I know of her,

1825
01:46:01,643 --> 01:46:02,873
she can be like a bulldozer.

1826
01:46:02,873 --> 01:46:04,903
But that was up to the Japan trip.

1827
01:46:04,903 --> 01:46:07,643
She got hurt a lot when they got
back to the house yesterday.

1828
01:46:07,643 --> 01:46:10,023
So, she won't text him today.

1829
01:46:10,023 --> 01:46:11,823
I'll listen to SinB.

1830
01:46:11,823 --> 01:46:13,263
Me?

1831
01:46:13,263 --> 01:46:14,923
Throw the bomb. The bomb.

1832
01:46:14,923 --> 01:46:19,293
As you've said, with So Yun's personality,

1833
01:46:19,293 --> 01:46:22,893
I think she'd still text Wu Yeol.

1834
01:46:22,893 --> 01:46:25,413
Let's go with what SinB said.

1835
01:46:25,413 --> 01:46:26,913
What if I'm wrong!

1836
01:46:26,913 --> 01:46:29,743
Let's just go with what we said.

1837
01:46:29,743 --> 01:46:31,763
Then, So Yun will choose Wu Yeol.

1838
01:46:31,763 --> 01:46:34,573
I don't think that, but I'll go with it.

1839
01:46:34,573 --> 01:46:36,773
- I think Jun Hyeon will text Yu Gyeong.
- Totally.

1840
01:46:36,773 --> 01:46:38,993
- I think he'll text Yu Gyeong.
- Me, too.

1841
01:46:38,993 --> 01:46:41,193
Then, let's go with Yu Gyeong.

1842
01:46:41,193 --> 01:46:43,813
Jun Hyeon for Yu Gyeong? That could be.

1843
01:46:43,813 --> 01:46:45,923
- This is hard.
- I don't know about this.

1844
01:46:45,923 --> 01:46:48,363
Did we get this right?

1845
01:46:56,653 --> 01:46:59,253
- Cute puppy.
- Wait! There's something.

1846
01:46:59,253 --> 01:47:01,173
What is it?

1847
01:47:01,173 --> 01:47:04,263
[A mysterious postcard is stuck
in Yu Gyeong's book]

1848
01:47:04,263 --> 01:47:06,773
[The Bridges of Madison County]

1849
01:47:06,773 --> 01:47:08,363
What is it?

1850
01:47:09,853 --> 01:47:11,843
[This morning]

1851
01:47:11,843 --> 01:47:12,833
Who is it?

1852
01:47:12,833 --> 01:47:16,253
[Thinking]

1853
01:47:20,233 --> 01:47:22,593
[Seong Min left a postcard
before going to work]

1854
01:47:22,593 --> 01:47:24,643
He left her a letter?

1855
01:47:26,103 --> 01:47:27,113
Really?

1856
01:47:27,113 --> 01:47:28,633
Wait a minute.

1857
01:47:28,633 --> 01:47:30,553
It's too noisy upstairs.

1858
01:47:30,553 --> 01:47:33,003
Gyu Ri said she'd take a nap.

1859
01:47:33,003 --> 01:47:37,763
[Seo Won worries about Gyu Ri]

1860
01:47:37,763 --> 01:47:40,693
I feel bad since she went out with me again.

1861
01:47:40,693 --> 01:47:42,673
I feel like
I'm taking away her sleeping time.

1862
01:47:42,673 --> 01:47:44,983
- Do what you need to do.
- Seo Won is so kind.

1863
01:47:44,983 --> 01:47:47,133
I just need to work hard at my job.

1864
01:47:48,103 --> 01:47:52,363
- So, I can buy tasty food on our date.
- So cute.

1865
01:47:52,363 --> 01:47:55,343
Everyone is having such a hard time.

1866
01:47:55,343 --> 01:47:57,893
[Rustle]

1867
01:47:58,593 --> 01:48:01,503
[Salt Bread: Let's have more fun
going forward]

1868
01:48:01,503 --> 01:48:05,243
They're texting each other
in front of the other.

1869
01:48:05,243 --> 01:48:08,323
- We connected.
- Are they at peace now?

1870
01:48:09,753 --> 01:48:12,443
[Busy Hamster: I'm rooting for
your new start at your job!]

1871
01:48:12,443 --> 01:48:14,283
[Good luck this week!]

1872
01:48:14,283 --> 01:48:16,743
Oh, great.

1873
01:48:16,743 --> 01:48:19,093
[Busy Hamster]

1874
01:48:24,383 --> 01:48:28,183
[Tired Camel: Pretty scarf]

1875
01:48:28,183 --> 01:48:33,443
Yes. This one was pretty straightforward.

1876
01:48:34,513 --> 01:48:39,013
[Dried Sweet Potato: Thank you. Sleep tight.]

1877
01:48:39,013 --> 01:48:42,133
[Dried Sweet Potato]

1878
01:48:42,133 --> 01:48:44,373
Gyu Ri. Let's go.

1879
01:48:45,263 --> 01:48:48,333
[Sleepy Bear: Can't wait until tomorrow!]

1880
01:48:48,333 --> 01:48:51,303
- Seong Min.
- "Can't wait until tomorrow!"

1881
01:48:51,303 --> 01:48:53,673
From Min Ju.

1882
01:48:57,603 --> 01:49:00,343
[Pure Rabbit: I had fun talking today]

1883
01:49:00,943 --> 01:49:05,403
[Pure Rabbit]

1884
01:49:05,403 --> 01:49:07,193
[Can't believe their eyes]

1885
01:49:07,193 --> 01:49:09,073
[So Yu texted Seong Min?]

1886
01:49:09,073 --> 01:49:11,063
[Totally unexpected]

1887
01:49:11,063 --> 01:49:14,613
- I did say it wouldn't be Wu Yeol.
- Kim Seong Min?

1888
01:49:14,613 --> 01:49:16,173
She can't just throw it out there.

1889
01:49:16,173 --> 01:49:18,233
We couldn't have guessed Seong Min.

1890
01:49:18,233 --> 01:49:20,253
What's the deal?

1891
01:49:20,253 --> 01:49:23,163
He's in shock.

1892
01:49:23,163 --> 01:49:25,423
We never even imagined.

1893
01:49:27,043 --> 01:49:29,573
[Beluga of the Forest:
Eat well and sleep well]

1894
01:49:30,153 --> 01:49:34,593
[Beluga of the Forest]

1895
01:49:34,593 --> 01:49:36,253
Oh? What's this? What's going on?

1896
01:49:36,253 --> 01:49:39,153
- Min Ju?
- Chaos!

1897
01:49:39,153 --> 01:49:41,263
Today is all over the place.

1898
01:49:41,263 --> 01:49:43,923
[This can't be]

1899
01:49:43,923 --> 01:49:45,893
Is this how it goes?

1900
01:49:45,893 --> 01:49:48,223
It's not like this, but today is weird.

1901
01:49:48,223 --> 01:49:50,163
Let's analyze their state of mind.

1902
01:49:50,163 --> 01:49:54,123
As Eana said earlier, So Yun likes Wu Yeol,

1903
01:49:54,123 --> 01:49:56,303
but she wouldn't pick him.

1904
01:49:56,303 --> 01:49:57,633
But why Seong Min?

1905
01:49:57,633 --> 01:49:59,333
Then, is this meaningless?

1906
01:49:59,333 --> 01:50:01,373
The important point for today is

1907
01:50:01,373 --> 01:50:05,333
the fact that they didn't text the
person of their interest.

1908
01:50:05,333 --> 01:50:07,003
Jun Hyeon, too?

1909
01:50:07,003 --> 01:50:08,993
But I get why Jun Hyeon texted Min Ju.

1910
01:50:08,993 --> 01:50:13,683
[Jun Hyeon came to empathize with Min Ju]

1911
01:50:13,683 --> 01:50:14,903
That could happen.

1912
01:50:14,903 --> 01:50:18,533
Does this mean
Jun Hyeon is bypassing Yu Gyeong?

1913
01:50:18,533 --> 01:50:21,023
- It's not that.
- He's finding out.

1914
01:50:21,023 --> 01:50:23,853
I'm curious as to why he texted her.

1915
01:50:23,853 --> 01:50:25,233
You look good here.

1916
01:50:25,233 --> 01:50:27,773
- This?
- It's so you.

1917
01:50:28,603 --> 01:50:32,203
[Overhearing laughter]

1918
01:50:32,963 --> 01:50:34,203
I can't stand it.

1919
01:50:34,203 --> 01:50:36,763
You can't stand it? Stand what?

1920
01:50:36,763 --> 01:50:38,833
- I can't stand to hear it.
- Why?

1921
01:50:38,833 --> 01:50:41,293
They're giggling in the tea room.

1922
01:50:41,293 --> 01:50:45,953
But you know, they're like that
on the day of their date.

1923
01:50:45,953 --> 01:50:47,633
Things can change anytime.

1924
01:50:47,633 --> 01:50:50,993
Right. But for some reason...

1925
01:50:50,993 --> 01:50:54,903
Min Ju is always looking after women
who have been hurt by Wu Yeol.

1926
01:50:54,903 --> 01:50:56,773
[Gyu Ri is back after Self Talk]

1927
01:50:56,773 --> 01:50:59,993
You know, things can change
drastically at any time.

1928
01:50:59,993 --> 01:51:02,903
I went on the date knowing that, but...

1929
01:51:02,903 --> 01:51:06,573
if they can get close like that overnight...

1930
01:51:07,573 --> 01:51:11,373
The feelings are growing more
since we're in the beginning phase.

1931
01:51:11,373 --> 01:51:15,993
I told you. I can't read Wu Yeol
at all among the men.

1932
01:51:15,993 --> 01:51:19,463
He's open right now.

1933
01:51:19,463 --> 01:51:23,133
He's open-ended. Seriously.

1934
01:51:23,133 --> 01:51:25,853
Don't you agree? He's totally open right now.

1935
01:51:25,853 --> 01:51:27,313
He keeps saying stuff to you, too. Right?

1936
01:51:27,313 --> 01:51:29,753
- But that's why...
- The women are discussing.

1937
01:51:29,753 --> 01:51:32,213
I've never fallen
for someone like him before.

1938
01:51:32,213 --> 01:51:35,003
He's doing that because we're
in the beginning phase.

1939
01:51:35,003 --> 01:51:39,093
Guys like that become devoted.
Once they fall...

1940
01:51:39,093 --> 01:51:43,793
Rather than being jealous over that,
what hurts me more is that

1941
01:51:43,793 --> 01:51:46,033
he just avoids me.

1942
01:51:46,033 --> 01:51:47,773
He won't even look me in the eye.

1943
01:51:47,773 --> 01:51:50,253
He won't talk to me.

1944
01:51:50,253 --> 01:51:51,983
When I talk to him, he avoids me.

1945
01:51:51,983 --> 01:51:54,393
He drew a really clear line with So Yun.

1946
01:51:54,393 --> 01:51:56,153
Where's Yu Gyeong?

1947
01:51:56,153 --> 01:51:58,613
Those two are in the tea room.

1948
01:51:58,613 --> 01:52:02,573
But it will change because two people
are interested in Yu Gyeong.

1949
01:52:02,573 --> 01:52:07,203
Seong Min and Jun Hyeon.

1950
01:52:07,203 --> 01:52:10,013
There are so many variables.

1951
01:52:10,013 --> 01:52:13,513
It's not just one or two. So, now is...

1952
01:52:13,513 --> 01:52:17,313
- Yu Gyeong has the most variables.
- She's telling her not to give up.

1953
01:52:17,313 --> 01:52:18,623
[Complicated]

1954
01:52:18,623 --> 01:52:20,363
Too tough.

1955
01:52:20,363 --> 01:52:23,403
- Everyone...
- Unni...

1956
01:52:23,403 --> 01:52:24,843
What do I do...

1957
01:52:24,843 --> 01:52:26,993
Why is she telling her?

1958
01:52:28,353 --> 01:52:30,033
Come on...

1959
01:52:30,033 --> 01:52:32,703
[Where should she start
to untangle these feelings?]

1960
01:52:32,703 --> 01:52:35,133
So Yun is struggling, too.

1961
01:52:37,463 --> 01:52:39,133
[They decide to watch a movie
in the tea room]

1962
01:52:39,133 --> 01:52:40,833
[Seong Min's beam projector]

1963
01:52:40,833 --> 01:52:44,383
This looks great like this.
It's so nice. So pretty.

1964
01:52:44,383 --> 01:52:47,123
I bought those two together.

1965
01:52:49,243 --> 01:52:50,463
[A few days ago]

1966
01:52:50,463 --> 01:52:53,883
I want to watch a movie upstairs.

1967
01:52:53,883 --> 01:52:56,213
They bought all the furniture
and appliances from here.

1968
01:52:56,213 --> 01:52:58,683
I like the house interior.

1969
01:52:58,683 --> 01:53:01,083
- This one.
- This?

1970
01:53:01,083 --> 01:53:04,193
It's the one that's downstairs.

1971
01:53:04,193 --> 01:53:06,683
[Thanks to Seong Min's beam projector,
the tea room became a theater]

1972
01:53:06,683 --> 01:53:08,643
It matches the shelf.

1973
01:53:08,643 --> 01:53:10,973
I know. I really want it in my place.

1974
01:53:10,973 --> 01:53:13,473
Nice. You did well.

1975
01:53:13,473 --> 01:53:15,773
Can you buy me one more?

1976
01:53:15,773 --> 01:53:18,253
Please!

1977
01:53:21,303 --> 01:53:24,783
I don't know how to put this on.

1978
01:53:27,853 --> 01:53:29,623
They're so set.

1979
01:53:29,623 --> 01:53:31,873
I don't think so.

1980
01:53:31,873 --> 01:53:34,153
So, now is your chance.

1981
01:53:34,153 --> 01:53:37,443
Are they doing that on purpose?

1982
01:53:37,443 --> 01:53:39,843
Should I go and see what Yu Gyeong
and Wu Yeol are up to?

1983
01:53:39,843 --> 01:53:41,463
Go look.

1984
01:53:45,813 --> 01:53:47,533
What are you doing?

1985
01:53:53,063 --> 01:53:55,113
I wanted to give you these.

1986
01:53:55,113 --> 01:53:56,483
It's hard.

1987
01:53:56,483 --> 01:53:58,723
I don't want to regret it.

1988
01:53:58,723 --> 01:54:01,503
I wasn't nervous, but I suddenly am.

1989
01:54:01,503 --> 01:54:03,553
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1990
01:54:03,553 --> 01:54:05,973
You'll regret things you don't do.

1991
01:54:05,973 --> 01:54:08,173
I was too closed up.

1992
01:54:08,173 --> 01:54:12,353
I saw you two downstairs...

1993
01:54:12,353 --> 01:54:14,853
Downstairs, I...

1994
01:54:14,853 --> 01:54:17,183
We were doing the dishes.

1995
01:54:18,418 --> 01:54:21,763
I wanted confirmation.

1996
01:54:21,763 --> 01:54:24,058
Are you interested?

1997
01:54:24,058 --> 01:54:25,758
We're similar.

1998
01:54:26,753 --> 01:54:29,733
I have something to say to you
one last time, Noona.
